7 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
8 // ----
9 // Pass to verify generated machine code. The following is checked: ----
10 // ----
11 // Operand counts: All explicit operands must be present. ----
12 // ----
13 // Register classes: All physical and virtual register operands must be ----
14 // compatible with the register class required by the instruction descriptor. ----
15 // ----
16 // Register live intervals: Registers must be defined only once, and must be ----
17 // defined before use. ----
18 // ----
19 // The machine code verifier is enabled with the command-line option ----
20 // -verify-machineinstrs. ----
21 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
22 ----

136 struct BBInfo { ----
137 // Is this MBB reachable from the MF entry point? ----
138 bool reachable = false; ----
139 ----
140 // Vregs that must be live in because they are used without being ----
141 // defined. Map value is the user. vregsLiveIn doesn't include regs ----
142 // that only are used by PHI nodes. ----
143 RegMap vregsLiveIn; ----
144 ----
145 // Regs killed in MBB. They may be defined again, and will then be in both ----
146 // regsKilled and regsLiveOut. ----
147 RegSet regsKilled; ----
148 ----
149 // Regs defined in MBB and live out. Note that vregs passing through may ----
150 // be live out without being mentioned here. ----
151 RegSet regsLiveOut; ----
152 ----
153 // Vregs that pass through MBB untouched. This set is disjoint from ----
154 // regsKilled and regsLiveOut. ----
155 RegSet vregsPassed; ----
156 ----
157 // Vregs that must pass through MBB because they are needed by a successor ----
158 // block. This set is disjoint from regsLiveOut. ----
159 RegSet vregsRequired; ----
160 ----
161 // Set versions of block's predecessor and successor lists. ----
162 BlockSet Preds, Succs; ----
163 ----
164 BBInfo() = default; 0
165 ----
166 // Add register to vregsRequired if it belongs there. Return true if ----
167 // anything changed. ----
168 bool addRequired(Register Reg) { 0
169 if (!Reg.isVirtual()) 0
170 return false; 0
171 if (regsLiveOut.count(Reg)) 0
172 return false; 0
173 return vregsRequired.insert(Reg).second; 0
174 } ----
175 ----
176 // Same for a full set. ----
177 bool addRequired(const RegSet &RS) { 0
178 bool Changed = false; 0
179 for (Register Reg : RS) 0
180 Changed |= addRequired(Reg); 0
181 return Changed; 0
182 } ----
183 ----
184 // Same for a full map. ----
185 bool addRequired(const RegMap &RM) { 0
186 bool Changed = false; 0
187 for (const auto &I : RM) 0
188 Changed |= addRequired(I.first); 0
189 return Changed; 0
190 } ----
191 ----
192 // Live-out registers are either in regsLiveOut or vregsPassed. ----
193 bool isLiveOut(Register Reg) const { 0
194 return regsLiveOut.count(Reg) || vregsPassed.count(Reg); 0
195 } ----
196 }; ----
197 ----
198 // Extra register info per MBB. ----
199 DenseMap MBBInfoMap; ----
200 ----
201 bool isReserved(Register Reg) { 0
202 return Reg.id() < regsReserved.size() && regsReserved.test(Reg.id()); 0
203 } ----
204 ----
205 bool isAllocatable(Register Reg) const { 0
206 return Reg.id() < TRI->getNumRegs() && TRI->isInAllocatableClass(Reg) && 0
207 !regsReserved.test(Reg.id()); 0
208 } ----

305 bool runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) override { 0
306 // Skip functions that have known verification problems. ----
307 // FIXME: Remove this mechanism when all problematic passes have been ----
308 // fixed. ----
309 if (MF.getProperties().hasProperty( 0
310 MachineFunctionProperties::Property::FailsVerification)) ----
311 return false; 0

343 ----
344 bool MachineFunction::verify(Pass *p, const char *Banner, bool AbortOnErrors) 0
345 const { ----
346 MachineFunction &MF = const_cast(*this); 0
347 unsigned FoundErrors = MachineVerifier(p, Banner).verify(MF); 0
348 if (AbortOnErrors && FoundErrors) 0
349 report_fatal_error("Found "+Twine(FoundErrors)+" machine code errors."); 0
350 return FoundErrors == 0; 0
351 } ----
352 ----
353 void MachineVerifier::verifySlotIndexes() const { 0
354 if (Indexes == nullptr) 0
355 return; 0
356 ----
357 // Ensure the IdxMBB list is sorted by slot indexes. ----
358 SlotIndex Last; 0
359 for (SlotIndexes::MBBIndexIterator I = Indexes->MBBIndexBegin(), 0
360 E = Indexes->MBBIndexEnd(); I != E; ++I) { 0
361 assert(!Last.isValid() || I->first > Last); 0
362 Last = I->first; 0
363 } ----
364 } ----
365 ----
366 void MachineVerifier::verifyProperties(const MachineFunction &MF) { 0
367 // If a pass has introduced virtual registers without clearing the ----
368 // NoVRegs property (or set it without allocating the vregs) ----
369 // then report an error. ----
370 if (MF.getProperties().hasProperty( 0
371 MachineFunctionProperties::Property::NoVRegs) && 0
372 MRI->getNumVirtRegs()) 0
373 report("Function has NoVRegs property but there are VReg operands", &MF); 0
374 } 0
375 ----
376 unsigned MachineVerifier::verify(const MachineFunction &MF) { 0
377 foundErrors = 0; 0
378 ----
379 this->MF = &MF; 0
380 TM = &MF.getTarget(); 0
381 TII = MF.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
382 TRI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
383 RBI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegBankInfo(); 0
384 MRI = &MF.getRegInfo(); 0
385 ----
386 const bool isFunctionFailedISel = MF.getProperties().hasProperty( 0
387 MachineFunctionProperties::Property::FailedISel); ----
388 ----
389 // If we're mid-GlobalISel and we already triggered the fallback path then ----
390 // it's expected that the MIR is somewhat broken but that's ok since we'll ----
391 // reset it and clear the FailedISel attribute in ResetMachineFunctions. ----
392 if (isFunctionFailedISel) 0
393 return foundErrors; 0
394 ----
395 isFunctionRegBankSelected = MF.getProperties().hasProperty( 0
396 MachineFunctionProperties::Property::RegBankSelected); ----
397 isFunctionSelected = MF.getProperties().hasProperty( 0
398 MachineFunctionProperties::Property::Selected); ----
399 isFunctionTracksDebugUserValues = MF.getProperties().hasProperty( 0
400 MachineFunctionProperties::Property::TracksDebugUserValues); ----
401 ----
402 LiveVars = nullptr; 0
403 LiveInts = nullptr; 0
404 LiveStks = nullptr; 0
405 Indexes = nullptr; 0
406 if (PASS) { 0
407 LiveInts = PASS->getAnalysisIfAvailable(); 0
408 // We don't want to verify LiveVariables if LiveIntervals is available. ----
409 if (!LiveInts) 0
410 LiveVars = PASS->getAnalysisIfAvailable(); 0
411 LiveStks = PASS->getAnalysisIfAvailable(); 0
412 Indexes = PASS->getAnalysisIfAvailable(); 0
413 } ----
414 ----
415 verifySlotIndexes(); 0
416 ----
417 verifyProperties(MF); 0
418 ----
419 visitMachineFunctionBefore(); 0
420 for (const MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) { 0
421 visitMachineBasicBlockBefore(&MBB); 0
422 // Keep track of the current bundle header. ----
423 const MachineInstr *CurBundle = nullptr; 0
424 // Do we expect the next instruction to be part of the same bundle? ----
425 bool InBundle = false; 0
426 ----
427 for (const MachineInstr &MI : MBB.instrs()) { 0
428 if (MI.getParent() != &MBB) { 0
429 report("Bad instruction parent pointer", &MBB); 0
430 errs() << "Instruction: " << MI; 0
431 continue; 0
432 } ----
433 ----
434 // Check for consistent bundle flags. ----
435 if (InBundle && !MI.isBundledWithPred()) 0
436 report("Missing BundledPred flag, " 0
437 "BundledSucc was set on predecessor", ----
438 &MI); ----
439 if (!InBundle && MI.isBundledWithPred()) 0
440 report("BundledPred flag is set, " 0
441 "but BundledSucc not set on predecessor", ----
442 &MI); ----
443 ----
444 // Is this a bundle header? ----
445 if (!MI.isInsideBundle()) { 0
446 if (CurBundle) 0
447 visitMachineBundleAfter(CurBundle); 0
448 CurBundle = &MI; 0
449 visitMachineBundleBefore(CurBundle); 0
450 } else if (!CurBundle) 0
451 report("No bundle header", &MI); 0
452 visitMachineInstrBefore(&MI); 0
453 for (unsigned I = 0, E = MI.getNumOperands(); I != E; ++I) { 0
454 const MachineOperand &Op = MI.getOperand(I); 0
455 if (Op.getParent() != &MI) { 0
456 // Make sure to use correct addOperand / removeOperand / ChangeTo ----
457 // functions when replacing operands of a MachineInstr. ----
458 report("Instruction has operand with wrong parent set", &MI); 0
459 } ----
460 ----
461 visitMachineOperand(&Op, I); 0
462 } ----
463 ----
464 // Was this the last bundled instruction? ----
465 InBundle = MI.isBundledWithSucc(); 0
466 } ----
467 if (CurBundle) 0
468 visitMachineBundleAfter(CurBundle); 0
469 if (InBundle) 0
470 report("BundledSucc flag set on last instruction in block", &MBB.back()); 0
471 visitMachineBasicBlockAfter(&MBB); 0
472 } ----
473 visitMachineFunctionAfter(); 0
474 ----
475 // Clean up. ----
476 regsLive.clear(); 0
477 regsDefined.clear(); 0
478 regsDead.clear(); 0
479 regsKilled.clear(); 0
480 regMasks.clear(); 0
481 MBBInfoMap.clear(); 0
482 ----
483 return foundErrors; 0
484 } ----
485 ----
486 void MachineVerifier::report(const char *msg, const MachineFunction *MF) { 0
487 assert(MF); 0
488 errs() << '\n'; 0
489 if (!foundErrors++) { 0
490 if (Banner) 0
491 errs() << "# " << Banner << '\n'; 0
492 if (LiveInts != nullptr) 0
493 LiveInts->print(errs()); 0
494 else ----
495 MF->print(errs(), Indexes); 0
496 } ----
497 errs() << "*** Bad machine code: " << msg << " ***\n" 0
498 << "- function: " << MF->getName() << "\n"; 0
499 } 0

506 if (Indexes) 0

510 } 0

581 ----
582 void MachineVerifier::markReachable(const MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
583 BBInfo &MInfo = MBBInfoMap[MBB]; 0
584 if (!MInfo.reachable) { 0
585 MInfo.reachable = true; 0
586 for (const MachineBasicBlock *Succ : MBB->successors()) 0
587 markReachable(Succ); 0
588 } ----
589 } 0
590 ----
591 void MachineVerifier::visitMachineFunctionBefore() { 0
592 lastIndex = SlotIndex(); 0
593 regsReserved = MRI->reservedRegsFrozen() ? MRI->getReservedRegs() 0
594 : TRI->getReservedRegs(*MF); 0
595 ----
596 if (!MF->empty()) 0
597 markReachable(&MF->front()); 0
598 ----
599 // Build a set of the basic blocks in the function. ----
600 FunctionBlocks.clear(); 0
601 for (const auto &MBB : *MF) { 0
602 FunctionBlocks.insert(&MBB); 0
603 BBInfo &MInfo = MBBInfoMap[&MBB]; 0
604 ----
605 MInfo.Preds.insert(MBB.pred_begin(), MBB.pred_end()); 0
606 if (MInfo.Preds.size() != MBB.pred_size()) 0
607 report("MBB has duplicate entries in its predecessor list.", &MBB); 0
608 ----
609 MInfo.Succs.insert(MBB.succ_begin(), MBB.succ_end()); 0
610 if (MInfo.Succs.size() != MBB.succ_size()) 0
611 report("MBB has duplicate entries in its successor list.", &MBB); 0
612 } ----
613 ----
614 // Check that the register use lists are sane. ----
615 MRI->verifyUseLists(); 0
616 ----
617 if (!MF->empty()) 0
618 verifyStackFrame(); 0
619 } 0
620 ----
621 void ----
622 MachineVerifier::visitMachineBasicBlockBefore(const MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
623 FirstTerminator = nullptr; 0
624 FirstNonPHI = nullptr; 0
625 ----
626 if (!MF->getProperties().hasProperty( 0
627 MachineFunctionProperties::Property::NoPHIs) && MRI->tracksLiveness()) { 0
628 // If this block has allocatable physical registers live-in, check that ----
629 // it is an entry block or landing pad. ----
630 for (const auto &LI : MBB->liveins()) { 0
631 if (isAllocatable(LI.PhysReg) && !MBB->isEHPad() && 0
632 MBB->getIterator() != MBB->getParent()->begin() && 0
633 !MBB->isInlineAsmBrIndirectTarget()) { 0
634 report("MBB has allocatable live-in, but isn't entry, landing-pad, or " 0
635 "inlineasm-br-indirect-target.", ----
636 MBB); ----
637 report_context(LI.PhysReg); 0
638 } ----
639 } ----
640 } ----
641 ----
642 if (MBB->isIRBlockAddressTaken()) { 0
643 if (!MBB->getAddressTakenIRBlock()->hasAddressTaken()) 0
644 report("ir-block-address-taken is associated with basic block not used by " 0
645 "a blockaddress.", ----
646 MBB); ----
647 } ----
648 ----
649 // Count the number of landing pad successors. ----
650 SmallPtrSet LandingPadSuccs; 0
651 for (const auto *succ : MBB->successors()) { 0
652 if (succ->isEHPad()) 0
653 LandingPadSuccs.insert(succ); 0
654 if (!FunctionBlocks.count(succ)) 0
655 report("MBB has successor that isn't part of the function.", MBB); 0
656 if (!MBBInfoMap[succ].Preds.count(MBB)) { 0
657 report("Inconsistent CFG", MBB); 0
658 errs() << "MBB is not in the predecessor list of the successor " 0
659 << printMBBReference(*succ) << ".\n"; 0
660 } ----
661 } ----
662 ----
663 // Check the predecessor list. ----
664 for (const MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB->predecessors()) { 0
665 if (!FunctionBlocks.count(Pred)) 0
666 report("MBB has predecessor that isn't part of the function.", MBB); 0
667 if (!MBBInfoMap[Pred].Succs.count(MBB)) { 0
668 report("Inconsistent CFG", MBB); 0
669 errs() << "MBB is not in the successor list of the predecessor " 0
670 << printMBBReference(*Pred) << ".\n"; 0
671 } ----
672 } ----
673 ----
674 const MCAsmInfo *AsmInfo = TM->getMCAsmInfo(); 0
675 const BasicBlock *BB = MBB->getBasicBlock(); 0
676 const Function &F = MF->getFunction(); 0
677 if (LandingPadSuccs.size() > 1 && 0
678 !(AsmInfo && 0
679 AsmInfo->getExceptionHandlingType() == ExceptionHandling::SjLj && 0
680 BB && isa(BB->getTerminator())) && 0
681 !isScopedEHPersonality(classifyEHPersonality(F.getPersonalityFn()))) 0
682 report("MBB has more than one landing pad successor", MBB); 0
683 ----
684 // Call analyzeBranch. If it succeeds, there several more conditions to check. ----
685 MachineBasicBlock *TBB = nullptr, *FBB = nullptr; 0
686 SmallVector Cond; 0
687 if (!TII->analyzeBranch(*const_cast(MBB), TBB, FBB, 0
688 Cond)) { ----
689 // Ok, analyzeBranch thinks it knows what's going on with this block. Let's ----
690 // check whether its answers match up with reality. ----
691 if (!TBB && !FBB) { 0
692 // Block falls through to its successor. ----
693 if (!MBB->empty() && MBB->back().isBarrier() && 0
694 !TII->isPredicated(MBB->back())) { 0
695 report("MBB exits via unconditional fall-through but ends with a " 0
696 "barrier instruction!", MBB); ----
697 } ----
698 if (!Cond.empty()) { 0
699 report("MBB exits via unconditional fall-through but has a condition!", 0
700 MBB); ----
701 } ----
702 } else if (TBB && !FBB && Cond.empty()) { 0
703 // Block unconditionally branches somewhere. ----
704 if (MBB->empty()) { 0
705 report("MBB exits via unconditional branch but doesn't contain " 0
706 "any instructions!", MBB); ----
707 } else if (!MBB->back().isBarrier()) { 0
708 report("MBB exits via unconditional branch but doesn't end with a " 0
709 "barrier instruction!", MBB); ----
710 } else if (!MBB->back().isTerminator()) { 0
711 report("MBB exits via unconditional branch but the branch isn't a " 0
712 "terminator instruction!", MBB); ----
713 } ----
714 } else if (TBB && !FBB && !Cond.empty()) { 0
715 // Block conditionally branches somewhere, otherwise falls through. ----
716 if (MBB->empty()) { 0
717 report("MBB exits via conditional branch/fall-through but doesn't " 0
718 "contain any instructions!", MBB); ----
719 } else if (MBB->back().isBarrier()) { 0
720 report("MBB exits via conditional branch/fall-through but ends with a " 0
721 "barrier instruction!", MBB); ----
722 } else if (!MBB->back().isTerminator()) { 0
723 report("MBB exits via conditional branch/fall-through but the branch " 0
724 "isn't a terminator instruction!", MBB); ----
725 } ----
726 } else if (TBB && FBB) { 0
727 // Block conditionally branches somewhere, otherwise branches ----
728 // somewhere else. ----
729 if (MBB->empty()) { 0
730 report("MBB exits via conditional branch/branch but doesn't " 0
731 "contain any instructions!", MBB); ----
732 } else if (!MBB->back().isBarrier()) { 0
733 report("MBB exits via conditional branch/branch but doesn't end with a " 0
734 "barrier instruction!", MBB); ----
735 } else if (!MBB->back().isTerminator()) { 0
736 report("MBB exits via conditional branch/branch but the branch " 0
737 "isn't a terminator instruction!", MBB); ----
738 } ----
739 if (Cond.empty()) { 0
740 report("MBB exits via conditional branch/branch but there's no " 0
741 "condition!", MBB); ----
742 } ----
743 } else { ----
744 report("analyzeBranch returned invalid data!", MBB); 0
745 } ----
746 ----
747 // Now check that the successors match up with the answers reported by ----
748 // analyzeBranch. ----
749 if (TBB && !MBB->isSuccessor(TBB)) 0
750 report("MBB exits via jump or conditional branch, but its target isn't a " 0
751 "CFG successor!", ----
752 MBB); ----
753 if (FBB && !MBB->isSuccessor(FBB)) 0
754 report("MBB exits via conditional branch, but its target isn't a CFG " 0
755 "successor!", ----
756 MBB); ----
757 ----
758 // There might be a fallthrough to the next block if there's either no ----
759 // unconditional true branch, or if there's a condition, and one of the ----
760 // branches is missing. ----
761 bool Fallthrough = !TBB || (!Cond.empty() && !FBB); 0
762 ----
763 // A conditional fallthrough must be an actual CFG successor, not ----
764 // unreachable. (Conversely, an unconditional fallthrough might not really ----
765 // be a successor, because the block might end in unreachable.) ----
766 if (!Cond.empty() && !FBB) { 0
767 MachineFunction::const_iterator MBBI = std::next(MBB->getIterator()); 0
768 if (MBBI == MF->end()) { 0
769 report("MBB conditionally falls through out of function!", MBB); 0
770 } else if (!MBB->isSuccessor(&*MBBI)) 0
771 report("MBB exits via conditional branch/fall-through but the CFG " 0
772 "successors don't match the actual successors!", ----
773 MBB); ----
774 } ----
775 ----
776 // Verify that there aren't any extra un-accounted-for successors. ----
777 for (const MachineBasicBlock *SuccMBB : MBB->successors()) { 0
778 // If this successor is one of the branch targets, it's okay. ----
779 if (SuccMBB == TBB || SuccMBB == FBB) 0
780 continue; 0
781 // If we might have a fallthrough, and the successor is the fallthrough ----
782 // block, that's also ok. ----
783 if (Fallthrough && SuccMBB == MBB->getNextNode()) 0
784 continue; 0
785 // Also accept successors which are for exception-handling or might be ----
786 // inlineasm_br targets. ----
787 if (SuccMBB->isEHPad() || SuccMBB->isInlineAsmBrIndirectTarget()) 0
788 continue; 0
789 report("MBB has unexpected successors which are not branch targets, " 0
790 "fallthrough, EHPads, or inlineasm_br targets.", ----
791 MBB); ----
792 } ----
793 } ----
794 ----
795 regsLive.clear(); 0
796 if (MRI->tracksLiveness()) { 0
797 for (const auto &LI : MBB->liveins()) { 0
798 if (!Register::isPhysicalRegister(LI.PhysReg)) { 0
799 report("MBB live-in list contains non-physical register", MBB); 0
800 continue; 0
801 } ----
802 for (const MCPhysReg &SubReg : TRI->subregs_inclusive(LI.PhysReg)) 0
803 regsLive.insert(SubReg); 0
804 } ----
805 } ----
806 ----
807 const MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF->getFrameInfo(); 0
808 BitVector PR = MFI.getPristineRegs(*MF); 0
809 for (unsigned I : PR.set_bits()) { 0
810 for (const MCPhysReg &SubReg : TRI->subregs_inclusive(I)) 0
811 regsLive.insert(SubReg); 0
812 } ----
813 ----
814 regsKilled.clear(); 0
815 regsDefined.clear(); 0
816 ----
817 if (Indexes) 0
818 lastIndex = Indexes->getMBBStartIdx(MBB); 0
819 } 0
820 ----
821 // This function gets called for all bundle headers, including normal ----
822 // stand-alone unbundled instructions. ----
823 void MachineVerifier::visitMachineBundleBefore(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
824 if (Indexes && Indexes->hasIndex(*MI)) { 0
825 SlotIndex idx = Indexes->getInstructionIndex(*MI); 0
826 if (!(idx > lastIndex)) { 0
827 report("Instruction index out of order", MI); 0
828 errs() << "Last instruction was at " << lastIndex << '\n'; 0
829 } ----
830 lastIndex = idx; 0
831 } ----
832 ----
833 // Ensure non-terminators don't follow terminators. ----
834 if (MI->isTerminator()) { 0
835 if (!FirstTerminator) 0
836 FirstTerminator = MI; 0
837 } else if (FirstTerminator) { 0
838 // For GlobalISel, G_INVOKE_REGION_START is a terminator that we allow to ----
839 // precede non-terminators. ----
840 if (FirstTerminator->getOpcode() != TargetOpcode::G_INVOKE_REGION_START) { 0
841 report("Non-terminator instruction after the first terminator", MI); 0
842 errs() << "First terminator was:\t" << *FirstTerminator; 0
843 } ----
844 } ----
845 } 0
846 ----
847 // The operands on an INLINEASM instruction must follow a template. ----
848 // Verify that the flag operands make sense. ----
849 void MachineVerifier::verifyInlineAsm(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
850 // The first two operands on INLINEASM are the asm string and global flags. ----
851 if (MI->getNumOperands() < 2) { 0
852 report("Too few operands on inline asm", MI); 0
853 return; 0
854 } ----
855 if (!MI->getOperand(0).isSymbol()) 0
856 report("Asm string must be an external symbol", MI); 0
857 if (!MI->getOperand(1).isImm()) 0
858 report("Asm flags must be an immediate", MI); 0
859 // Allowed flags are Extra_HasSideEffects = 1, Extra_IsAlignStack = 2, ----
860 // Extra_AsmDialect = 4, Extra_MayLoad = 8, and Extra_MayStore = 16, ----
861 // and Extra_IsConvergent = 32. ----
862 if (!isUInt<6>(MI->getOperand(1).getImm())) 0
863 report("Unknown asm flags", &MI->getOperand(1), 1); 0
864 ----
865 static_assert(InlineAsm::MIOp_FirstOperand == 2, "Asm format changed"); ----
866 ----
867 unsigned OpNo = InlineAsm::MIOp_FirstOperand; 0
868 unsigned NumOps; ----
869 for (unsigned e = MI->getNumOperands(); OpNo < e; OpNo += NumOps) { 0
870 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(OpNo); 0
871 // There may be implicit ops after the fixed operands. ----
872 if (!MO.isImm()) 0
873 break; 0
874 NumOps = 1 + InlineAsm::getNumOperandRegisters(MO.getImm()); 0
875 } ----
876 ----
877 if (OpNo > MI->getNumOperands()) 0
878 report("Missing operands in last group", MI); 0
879 ----
880 // An optional MDNode follows the groups. ----
881 if (OpNo < MI->getNumOperands() && MI->getOperand(OpNo).isMetadata()) 0
882 ++OpNo; 0
883 ----
884 // All trailing operands must be implicit registers. ----
885 for (unsigned e = MI->getNumOperands(); OpNo < e; ++OpNo) { 0
886 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(OpNo); 0
887 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.isImplicit()) 0
888 report("Expected implicit register after groups", &MO, OpNo); 0
889 } ----
890 ----
891 if (MI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::INLINEASM_BR) { 0
892 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI->getParent(); 0
893 ----
894 for (unsigned i = InlineAsm::MIOp_FirstOperand, e = MI->getNumOperands(); 0
895 i != e; ++i) { 0
896 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(i); 0
897 ----
898 if (!MO.isMBB()) 0
899 continue; 0
900 ----
901 // Check the successor & predecessor lists look ok, assume they are ----
902 // not. Find the indirect target without going through the successors. ----
903 const MachineBasicBlock *IndirectTargetMBB = MO.getMBB(); 0
904 if (!IndirectTargetMBB) { 0
905 report("INLINEASM_BR indirect target does not exist", &MO, i); 0
906 break; 0
907 } ----
908 ----
909 if (!MBB->isSuccessor(IndirectTargetMBB)) 0
910 report("INLINEASM_BR indirect target missing from successor list", &MO, 0
911 i); ----
912 ----
913 if (!IndirectTargetMBB->isPredecessor(MBB)) 0
914 report("INLINEASM_BR indirect target predecessor list missing parent", 0
915 &MO, i); ----
916 } ----
917 } ----
918 } ----
919 ----
920 bool MachineVerifier::verifyAllRegOpsScalar(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
921 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) { ----
922 if (none_of(MI.explicit_operands(), [&MRI](const MachineOperand &Op) { 0
923 if (!Op.isReg()) 0
924 return false; 0
925 const auto Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
926 if (Reg.isPhysical()) 0
927 return false; 0
928 return !MRI.getType(Reg).isScalar(); 0
929 })) ----
930 return true; 0
931 report("All register operands must have scalar types", &MI); 0
932 return false; 0
933 } ----
934 ----
935 /// Check that types are consistent when two operands need to have the same ----
936 /// number of vector elements. ----
937 /// \return true if the types are valid. ----
938 bool MachineVerifier::verifyVectorElementMatch(LLT Ty0, LLT Ty1, 0
939 const MachineInstr *MI) { ----
940 if (Ty0.isVector() != Ty1.isVector()) { 0
941 report("operand types must be all-vector or all-scalar", MI); 0
942 // Generally we try to report as many issues as possible at once, but in ----
943 // this case it's not clear what should we be comparing the size of the ----
944 // scalar with: the size of the whole vector or its lane. Instead of ----
945 // making an arbitrary choice and emitting not so helpful message, let's ----
946 // avoid the extra noise and stop here. ----
947 return false; 0
948 } ----
949 ----
950 if (Ty0.isVector() && Ty0.getNumElements() != Ty1.getNumElements()) { 0
951 report("operand types must preserve number of vector elements", MI); 0
952 return false; 0
953 } ----
954 ----
955 return true; 0
956 } ----
957 ----
958 void MachineVerifier::verifyPreISelGenericInstruction(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
959 if (isFunctionSelected) 0
960 report("Unexpected generic instruction in a Selected function", MI); 0
961 ----
962 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MI->getDesc(); 0
963 unsigned NumOps = MI->getNumOperands(); 0
964 ----
965 // Branches must reference a basic block if they are not indirect ----
966 if (MI->isBranch() && !MI->isIndirectBranch()) { 0
967 bool HasMBB = false; 0
968 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI->operands()) { 0
969 if (Op.isMBB()) { 0
970 HasMBB = true; 0
971 break; 0
972 } ----
973 } ----
974 ----
975 if (!HasMBB) { 0
976 report("Branch instruction is missing a basic block operand or " 0
977 "isIndirectBranch property", ----
978 MI); ----
979 } ----
980 } ----
981 ----
982 // Check types. ----
983 SmallVector Types; 0
984 for (unsigned I = 0, E = std::min(MCID.getNumOperands(), NumOps); 0
985 I != E; ++I) { 0
986 if (!MCID.operands()[I].isGenericType()) 0
987 continue; 0
988 // Generic instructions specify type equality constraints between some of ----
989 // their operands. Make sure these are consistent. ----
990 size_t TypeIdx = MCID.operands()[I].getGenericTypeIndex(); 0
991 Types.resize(std::max(TypeIdx + 1, Types.size())); 0
992 ----
993 const MachineOperand *MO = &MI->getOperand(I); 0
994 if (!MO->isReg()) { 0
995 report("generic instruction must use register operands", MI); 0
996 continue; 0
997 } ----
998 ----
999 LLT OpTy = MRI->getType(MO->getReg()); 0
1000 // Don't report a type mismatch if there is no actual mismatch, only a ----
1001 // type missing, to reduce noise: ----
1002 if (OpTy.isValid()) { 0
1003 // Only the first valid type for a type index will be printed: don't ----
1004 // overwrite it later so it's always clear which type was expected: ----
1005 if (!Types[TypeIdx].isValid()) 0
1006 Types[TypeIdx] = OpTy; 0
1007 else if (Types[TypeIdx] != OpTy) 0
1008 report("Type mismatch in generic instruction", MO, I, OpTy); 0
1009 } else { ----
1010 // Generic instructions must have types attached to their operands. ----
1011 report("Generic instruction is missing a virtual register type", MO, I); 0
1012 } ----
1013 } ----
1014 ----
1015 // Generic opcodes must not have physical register operands. ----
1016 for (unsigned I = 0; I < MI->getNumOperands(); ++I) { 0
1017 const MachineOperand *MO = &MI->getOperand(I); 0
1018 if (MO->isReg() && MO->getReg().isPhysical()) 0
1019 report("Generic instruction cannot have physical register", MO, I); 0
1020 } ----
1021 ----
1022 // Avoid out of bounds in checks below. This was already reported earlier. ----
1023 if (MI->getNumOperands() < MCID.getNumOperands()) 0
1024 return; 0
1025 ----
1026 StringRef ErrorInfo; 0
1027 if (!TII->verifyInstruction(*MI, ErrorInfo)) 0
1028 report(ErrorInfo.data(), MI); 0
1029 ----
1030 // Verify properties of various specific instruction types ----
1031 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
1032 switch (Opc) { 0
1033 case TargetOpcode::G_ASSERT_SEXT: 0
1034 case TargetOpcode::G_ASSERT_ZEXT: { ----
1035 std::string OpcName = ----
1036 Opc == TargetOpcode::G_ASSERT_ZEXT ? "G_ASSERT_ZEXT" : "G_ASSERT_SEXT"; 0
1037 if (!MI->getOperand(2).isImm()) { 0
1038 report(Twine(OpcName, " expects an immediate operand #2"), MI); 0
1039 break; 0
1040 } ----
1041 ----
1042 Register Dst = MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1043 Register Src = MI->getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1044 LLT SrcTy = MRI->getType(Src); 0
1045 int64_t Imm = MI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1046 if (Imm <= 0) { 0
1047 report(Twine(OpcName, " size must be >= 1"), MI); 0
1048 break; 0
1049 } ----
1050 ----
1051 if (Imm >= SrcTy.getScalarSizeInBits()) { 0
1052 report(Twine(OpcName, " size must be less than source bit width"), MI); 0
1053 break; 0
1054 } ----
1055 ----
1056 const RegisterBank *SrcRB = RBI->getRegBank(Src, *MRI, *TRI); 0
1057 const RegisterBank *DstRB = RBI->getRegBank(Dst, *MRI, *TRI); 0
1058 ----
1059 // Allow only the source bank to be set. ----
1060 if ((SrcRB && DstRB && SrcRB != DstRB) || (DstRB && !SrcRB)) { 0
1061 report(Twine(OpcName, " cannot change register bank"), MI); 0
1062 break; 0
1063 } ----
1064 ----
1065 // Don't allow a class change. Do allow member class->regbank. ----
1066 const TargetRegisterClass *DstRC = MRI->getRegClassOrNull(Dst); 0
1067 if (DstRC && DstRC != MRI->getRegClassOrNull(Src)) { 0
1068 report( 0
1069 Twine(OpcName, " source and destination register classes must match"), 0
1070 MI); ----
1071 break; 0
1072 } ----
1073 ----
1074 break; 0
1075 } 0
1076 ----
1077 case TargetOpcode::G_CONSTANT: 0
1078 case TargetOpcode::G_FCONSTANT: { ----
1079 LLT DstTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1080 if (DstTy.isVector()) 0
1081 report("Instruction cannot use a vector result type", MI); 0
1082 ----
1083 if (MI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_CONSTANT) { 0
1084 if (!MI->getOperand(1).isCImm()) { 0
1085 report("G_CONSTANT operand must be cimm", MI); 0
1086 break; 0
1087 } ----
1088 ----
1089 const ConstantInt *CI = MI->getOperand(1).getCImm(); 0
1090 if (CI->getBitWidth() != DstTy.getSizeInBits()) 0
1091 report("inconsistent constant size", MI); 0
1092 } else { ----
1093 if (!MI->getOperand(1).isFPImm()) { 0
1094 report("G_FCONSTANT operand must be fpimm", MI); 0
1095 break; 0
1096 } ----
1097 const ConstantFP *CF = MI->getOperand(1).getFPImm(); 0
1098 ----
1099 if (APFloat::getSizeInBits(CF->getValueAPF().getSemantics()) != 0
1100 DstTy.getSizeInBits()) { 0
1101 report("inconsistent constant size", MI); 0
1102 } ----
1103 } ----
1104 ----
1105 break; 0
1106 } ----
1107 case TargetOpcode::G_LOAD: 0
1108 case TargetOpcode::G_STORE: ----
1109 case TargetOpcode::G_ZEXTLOAD: ----
1110 case TargetOpcode::G_SEXTLOAD: { ----
1111 LLT ValTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1112 LLT PtrTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1113 if (!PtrTy.isPointer()) 0
1114 report("Generic memory instruction must access a pointer", MI); 0
1115 ----
1116 // Generic loads and stores must have a single MachineMemOperand ----
1117 // describing that access. ----
1118 if (!MI->hasOneMemOperand()) { 0
1119 report("Generic instruction accessing memory must have one mem operand", 0
1120 MI); ----
1121 } else { ----
1122 const MachineMemOperand &MMO = **MI->memoperands_begin(); 0
1123 if (MI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_ZEXTLOAD || 0
1124 MI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_SEXTLOAD) { 0
1125 if (MMO.getSizeInBits() >= ValTy.getSizeInBits()) 0
1126 report("Generic extload must have a narrower memory type", MI); 0
1127 } else if (MI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_LOAD) { 0
1128 if (MMO.getSize() > ValTy.getSizeInBytes()) 0
1129 report("load memory size cannot exceed result size", MI); 0
1130 } else if (MI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_STORE) { 0
1131 if (ValTy.getSizeInBytes() < MMO.getSize()) 0
1132 report("store memory size cannot exceed value size", MI); 0
1133 } ----
1134 ----
1135 const AtomicOrdering Order = MMO.getSuccessOrdering(); 0
1136 if (Opc == TargetOpcode::G_STORE) { 0
1137 if (Order == AtomicOrdering::Acquire || 0
1138 Order == AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease) ----
1139 report("atomic store cannot use acquire ordering", MI); 0
1140 ----
1141 } else { ----
1142 if (Order == AtomicOrdering::Release || 0
1143 Order == AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease) ----
1144 report("atomic load cannot use release ordering", MI); 0
1145 } ----
1146 } ----
1147 ----
1148 break; 0
1149 } ----
1150 case TargetOpcode::G_PHI: { 0
1151 LLT DstTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1152 if (!DstTy.isValid() || !all_of(drop_begin(MI->operands()), 0
1153 [this, &DstTy](const MachineOperand &MO) { 0
1154 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
1155 return true; 0
1156 LLT Ty = MRI->getType(MO.getReg()); 0
1157 if (!Ty.isValid() || (Ty != DstTy)) 0
1158 return false; 0
1159 return true; 0
1160 })) ----
1161 report("Generic Instruction G_PHI has operands with incompatible/missing " 0
1162 "types", ----
1163 MI); ----
1164 break; 0
1165 } ----
1166 case TargetOpcode::G_BITCAST: { 0
1167 LLT DstTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1168 LLT SrcTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1169 if (!DstTy.isValid() || !SrcTy.isValid()) 0
1170 break; 0
1171 ----
1172 if (SrcTy.isPointer() != DstTy.isPointer()) 0
1173 report("bitcast cannot convert between pointers and other types", MI); 0
1174 ----
1175 if (SrcTy.getSizeInBits() != DstTy.getSizeInBits()) 0
1176 report("bitcast sizes must match", MI); 0
1177 ----
1178 if (SrcTy == DstTy) 0
1179 report("bitcast must change the type", MI); 0
1180 ----
1181 break; 0
1182 } ----
1183 case TargetOpcode::G_INTTOPTR: 0
1184 case TargetOpcode::G_PTRTOINT: ----
1185 case TargetOpcode::G_ADDRSPACE_CAST: { ----
1186 LLT DstTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1187 LLT SrcTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1188 if (!DstTy.isValid() || !SrcTy.isValid()) 0
1189 break; 0
1190 ----
1191 verifyVectorElementMatch(DstTy, SrcTy, MI); 0
1192 ----
1193 DstTy = DstTy.getScalarType(); 0
1194 SrcTy = SrcTy.getScalarType(); 0
1195 ----
1196 if (MI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_INTTOPTR) { 0
1197 if (!DstTy.isPointer()) 0
1198 report("inttoptr result type must be a pointer", MI); 0
1199 if (SrcTy.isPointer()) 0
1200 report("inttoptr source type must not be a pointer", MI); 0
1201 } else if (MI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_PTRTOINT) { 0
1202 if (!SrcTy.isPointer()) 0
1203 report("ptrtoint source type must be a pointer", MI); 0
1204 if (DstTy.isPointer()) 0
1205 report("ptrtoint result type must not be a pointer", MI); 0
1206 } else { ----
1207 assert(MI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_ADDRSPACE_CAST); 0
1208 if (!SrcTy.isPointer() || !DstTy.isPointer()) 0
1209 report("addrspacecast types must be pointers", MI); 0
1210 else { ----
1211 if (SrcTy.getAddressSpace() == DstTy.getAddressSpace()) 0
1212 report("addrspacecast must convert different address spaces", MI); 0
1213 } ----
1214 } ----
1215 ----
1216 break; 0
1217 } ----
1218 case TargetOpcode::G_PTR_ADD: { 0
1219 LLT DstTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1220 LLT PtrTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1221 LLT OffsetTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(2).getReg()); 0
1222 if (!DstTy.isValid() || !PtrTy.isValid() || !OffsetTy.isValid()) 0
1223 break; 0
1224 ----
1225 if (!PtrTy.getScalarType().isPointer()) 0
1226 report("gep first operand must be a pointer", MI); 0
1227 ----
1228 if (OffsetTy.getScalarType().isPointer()) 0
1229 report("gep offset operand must not be a pointer", MI); 0
1230 ----
1231 // TODO: Is the offset allowed to be a scalar with a vector? ----
1232 break; 0
1233 } ----
1234 case TargetOpcode::G_PTRMASK: { 0
1235 LLT DstTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1236 LLT SrcTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1237 LLT MaskTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(2).getReg()); 0
1238 if (!DstTy.isValid() || !SrcTy.isValid() || !MaskTy.isValid()) 0
1239 break; 0
1240 ----
1241 if (!DstTy.getScalarType().isPointer()) 0
1242 report("ptrmask result type must be a pointer", MI); 0
1243 ----
1244 if (!MaskTy.getScalarType().isScalar()) 0
1245 report("ptrmask mask type must be an integer", MI); 0
1246 ----
1247 verifyVectorElementMatch(DstTy, MaskTy, MI); 0
1248 break; 0
1249 } ----
1250 case TargetOpcode::G_SEXT: 0
1251 case TargetOpcode::G_ZEXT: ----
1252 case TargetOpcode::G_ANYEXT: ----
1253 case TargetOpcode::G_TRUNC: ----
1254 case TargetOpcode::G_FPEXT: ----
1255 case TargetOpcode::G_FPTRUNC: { ----
1256 // Number of operands and presense of types is already checked (and ----
1257 // reported in case of any issues), so no need to report them again. As ----
1258 // we're trying to report as many issues as possible at once, however, the ----
1259 // instructions aren't guaranteed to have the right number of operands or ----
1260 // types attached to them at this point ----
1261 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 2 && "Expected 2 operands G_*{EXT,TRUNC}"); 0
1262 LLT DstTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1263 LLT SrcTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1264 if (!DstTy.isValid() || !SrcTy.isValid()) 0
1265 break; 0
1266 ----
1267 LLT DstElTy = DstTy.getScalarType(); 0
1268 LLT SrcElTy = SrcTy.getScalarType(); 0
1269 if (DstElTy.isPointer() || SrcElTy.isPointer()) 0
1270 report("Generic extend/truncate can not operate on pointers", MI); 0
1271 ----
1272 verifyVectorElementMatch(DstTy, SrcTy, MI); 0
1273 ----
1274 unsigned DstSize = DstElTy.getSizeInBits(); 0
1275 unsigned SrcSize = SrcElTy.getSizeInBits(); 0
1276 switch (MI->getOpcode()) { 0
1277 default: 0
1278 if (DstSize <= SrcSize) 0
1279 report("Generic extend has destination type no larger than source", MI); 0
1280 break; 0
1281 case TargetOpcode::G_TRUNC: 0
1282 case TargetOpcode::G_FPTRUNC: ----
1283 if (DstSize >= SrcSize) 0
1284 report("Generic truncate has destination type no smaller than source", 0
1285 MI); ----
1286 break; 0
1287 } ----
1288 break; 0
1289 } ----
1290 case TargetOpcode::G_SELECT: { 0
1291 LLT SelTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1292 LLT CondTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1293 if (!SelTy.isValid() || !CondTy.isValid()) 0
1294 break; 0
1295 ----
1296 // Scalar condition select on a vector is valid. ----
1297 if (CondTy.isVector()) 0
1298 verifyVectorElementMatch(SelTy, CondTy, MI); 0
1299 break; 0
1300 } ----
1301 case TargetOpcode::G_MERGE_VALUES: { 0
1302 // G_MERGE_VALUES should only be used to merge scalars into a larger scalar, ----
1303 // e.g. s2N = MERGE sN, sN ----
1304 // Merging multiple scalars into a vector is not allowed, should use ----
1305 // G_BUILD_VECTOR for that. ----
1306 LLT DstTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1307 LLT SrcTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1308 if (DstTy.isVector() || SrcTy.isVector()) 0
1309 report("G_MERGE_VALUES cannot operate on vectors", MI); 0
1310 ----
1311 const unsigned NumOps = MI->getNumOperands(); 0
1312 if (DstTy.getSizeInBits() != SrcTy.getSizeInBits() * (NumOps - 1)) 0
1313 report("G_MERGE_VALUES result size is inconsistent", MI); 0
1314 ----
1315 for (unsigned I = 2; I != NumOps; ++I) { 0
1316 if (MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(I).getReg()) != SrcTy) 0
1317 report("G_MERGE_VALUES source types do not match", MI); 0
1318 } ----
1319 ----
1320 break; 0
1321 } ----
1322 case TargetOpcode::G_UNMERGE_VALUES: { 0
1323 unsigned NumDsts = MI->getNumOperands() - 1; 0
1324 LLT DstTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1325 for (unsigned i = 1; i < NumDsts; ++i) { 0
1326 if (MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(i).getReg()) != DstTy) { 0
1327 report("G_UNMERGE_VALUES destination types do not match", MI); 0
1328 break; 0
1329 } ----
1330 } ----
1331 ----
1332 LLT SrcTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(NumDsts).getReg()); 0
1333 if (DstTy.isVector()) { 0
1334 // This case is the converse of G_CONCAT_VECTORS. ----
1335 if (!SrcTy.isVector() || SrcTy.getScalarType() != DstTy.getScalarType() || 0
1336 SrcTy.getNumElements() != NumDsts * DstTy.getNumElements()) 0
1337 report("G_UNMERGE_VALUES source operand does not match vector " 0
1338 "destination operands", ----
1339 MI); ----
1340 } else if (SrcTy.isVector()) { 0
1341 // This case is the converse of G_BUILD_VECTOR, but relaxed to allow ----
1342 // mismatched types as long as the total size matches: ----
1343 // %0:_(s64), %1:_(s64) = G_UNMERGE_VALUES %2:_(<4 x s32>) ----
1344 if (SrcTy.getSizeInBits() != NumDsts * DstTy.getSizeInBits()) 0
1345 report("G_UNMERGE_VALUES vector source operand does not match scalar " 0
1346 "destination operands", ----
1347 MI); ----
1348 } else { ----
1349 // This case is the converse of G_MERGE_VALUES. ----
1350 if (SrcTy.getSizeInBits() != NumDsts * DstTy.getSizeInBits()) { 0
1351 report("G_UNMERGE_VALUES scalar source operand does not match scalar " 0
1352 "destination operands", ----
1353 MI); ----
1354 } ----
1355 } ----
1356 break; 0
1357 } ----
1358 case TargetOpcode::G_BUILD_VECTOR: { 0
1359 // Source types must be scalars, dest type a vector. Total size of scalars ----
1360 // must match the dest vector size. ----
1361 LLT DstTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1362 LLT SrcEltTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1363 if (!DstTy.isVector() || SrcEltTy.isVector()) { 0
1364 report("G_BUILD_VECTOR must produce a vector from scalar operands", MI); 0
1365 break; 0
1366 } ----
1367 ----
1368 if (DstTy.getElementType() != SrcEltTy) 0
1369 report("G_BUILD_VECTOR result element type must match source type", MI); 0
1370 ----
1371 if (DstTy.getNumElements() != MI->getNumOperands() - 1) 0
1372 report("G_BUILD_VECTOR must have an operand for each elemement", MI); 0
1373 ----
1374 for (const MachineOperand &MO : llvm::drop_begin(MI->operands(), 2)) 0
1375 if (MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()) != MRI->getType(MO.getReg())) 0
1376 report("G_BUILD_VECTOR source operand types are not homogeneous", MI); 0
1377 ----
1378 break; 0
1379 } ----
1380 case TargetOpcode::G_BUILD_VECTOR_TRUNC: { 0
1381 // Source types must be scalars, dest type a vector. Scalar types must be ----
1382 // larger than the dest vector elt type, as this is a truncating operation. ----
1383 LLT DstTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1384 LLT SrcEltTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1385 if (!DstTy.isVector() || SrcEltTy.isVector()) 0
1386 report("G_BUILD_VECTOR_TRUNC must produce a vector from scalar operands", 0
1387 MI); ----
1388 for (const MachineOperand &MO : llvm::drop_begin(MI->operands(), 2)) 0
1389 if (MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()) != MRI->getType(MO.getReg())) 0
1390 report("G_BUILD_VECTOR_TRUNC source operand types are not homogeneous", 0
1391 MI); ----
1392 if (SrcEltTy.getSizeInBits() <= DstTy.getElementType().getSizeInBits()) 0
1393 report("G_BUILD_VECTOR_TRUNC source operand types are not larger than " 0
1394 "dest elt type", ----
1395 MI); ----
1396 break; 0
1397 } ----
1398 case TargetOpcode::G_CONCAT_VECTORS: { 0
1399 // Source types should be vectors, and total size should match the dest ----
1400 // vector size. ----
1401 LLT DstTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1402 LLT SrcTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1403 if (!DstTy.isVector() || !SrcTy.isVector()) 0
1404 report("G_CONCAT_VECTOR requires vector source and destination operands", 0
1405 MI); ----
1406 ----
1407 if (MI->getNumOperands() < 3) 0
1408 report("G_CONCAT_VECTOR requires at least 2 source operands", MI); 0
1409 ----
1410 for (const MachineOperand &MO : llvm::drop_begin(MI->operands(), 2)) 0
1411 if (MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()) != MRI->getType(MO.getReg())) 0
1412 report("G_CONCAT_VECTOR source operand types are not homogeneous", MI); 0
1413 if (DstTy.getNumElements() != 0
1414 SrcTy.getNumElements() * (MI->getNumOperands() - 1)) 0
1415 report("G_CONCAT_VECTOR num dest and source elements should match", MI); 0
1416 break; 0
1417 } ----
1418 case TargetOpcode::G_ICMP: 0

1495 case TargetOpcode::G_INTRINSIC: 0
1496 case TargetOpcode::G_INTRINSIC_W_SIDE_EFFECTS: { ----

1498 // interface requires passing in IR types for mangling. ----
1499 const MachineOperand &IntrIDOp = MI->getOperand(MI->getNumExplicitDefs()); 0
1500 if (!IntrIDOp.isIntrinsicID()) { 0
