1719 verifyAllRegOpsScalar(*MI, *MRI); 0
1720 break; 0
1721 } ----
1722 case TargetOpcode::G_IS_FPCLASS: { 0
1723 LLT DestTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1724 LLT DestEltTy = DestTy.getScalarType(); 0
1725 if (!DestEltTy.isScalar()) { 0
1726 report("Destination must be a scalar or vector of scalars", MI); 0
1727 break; 0
1728 } ----
1729 LLT SrcTy = MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1730 LLT SrcEltTy = SrcTy.getScalarType(); 0
1731 if (!SrcEltTy.isScalar()) { 0
1732 report("Source must be a scalar or vector of scalars", MI); 0
1733 break; 0
1734 } ----
1735 if (!verifyVectorElementMatch(DestTy, SrcTy, MI)) 0
1736 break; 0
1737 const MachineOperand &TestMO = MI->getOperand(2); 0
1738 if (!TestMO.isImm()) { 0
1739 report("floating-point class set (operand 2) must be an immediate", MI); 0
1740 break; 0
1741 } ----
1742 int64_t Test = TestMO.getImm(); 0
1743 if (Test < 0 || Test > fcAllFlags) { 0
1744 report("Incorrect floating-point class set (operand 2)", MI); 0
1745 break; 0
1746 } ----
1747 break; 0
1748 } ----
1749 case TargetOpcode::G_ASSERT_ALIGN: { 0
1750 if (MI->getOperand(2).getImm() < 1) 0
1751 report("alignment immediate must be >= 1", MI); 0
1752 break; 0
1753 } ----
1754 case TargetOpcode::G_CONSTANT_POOL: { 0
1755 if (!MI->getOperand(1).isCPI()) 0
1756 report("Src operand 1 must be a constant pool index", MI); 0
1757 if (!MRI->getType(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()).isPointer()) 0
1758 report("Dst operand 0 must be a pointer", MI); 0
1759 break; 0
1760 } ----
1761 default: 0
1762 break; 0
1763 } ----
1764 } 0
1765 ----
1766 void MachineVerifier::visitMachineInstrBefore(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1767 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MI->getDesc(); 0
1768 if (MI->getNumOperands() < MCID.getNumOperands()) { 0
1769 report("Too few operands", MI); 0
1770 errs() << MCID.getNumOperands() << " operands expected, but " 0
1771 << MI->getNumOperands() << " given.\n"; 0
1772 } ----
1773 ----
1774 if (MI->isPHI()) { 0
1775 if (MF->getProperties().hasProperty( 0
1776 MachineFunctionProperties::Property::NoPHIs)) ----
1777 report("Found PHI instruction with NoPHIs property set", MI); 0
1778 ----
1779 if (FirstNonPHI) 0
1780 report("Found PHI instruction after non-PHI", MI); 0
1781 } else if (FirstNonPHI == nullptr) 0
1782 FirstNonPHI = MI; 0
1783 ----
1784 // Check the tied operands. ----
1785 if (MI->isInlineAsm()) 0
1786 verifyInlineAsm(MI); 0
1787 ----
1788 // Check that unspillable terminators define a reg and have at most one use. ----
1789 if (TII->isUnspillableTerminator(MI)) { 0
1790 if (!MI->getOperand(0).isReg() || !MI->getOperand(0).isDef()) 0
1791 report("Unspillable Terminator does not define a reg", MI); 0
1792 Register Def = MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1793 if (Def.isVirtual() && 0
1794 !MF->getProperties().hasProperty( 0
1795 MachineFunctionProperties::Property::NoPHIs) && 0
1796 std::distance(MRI->use_nodbg_begin(Def), MRI->use_nodbg_end()) > 1) 0
1797 report("Unspillable Terminator expected to have at most one use!", MI); 0
1798 } ----
1799 ----
1800 // A fully-formed DBG_VALUE must have a location. Ignore partially formed ----
1801 // DBG_VALUEs: these are convenient to use in tests, but should never get ----
1802 // generated. ----
1803 if (MI->isDebugValue() && MI->getNumOperands() == 4) 0
1804 if (!MI->getDebugLoc()) 0
1805 report("Missing DebugLoc for debug instruction", MI); 0
1806 ----
1807 // Meta instructions should never be the subject of debug value tracking, ----
1808 // they don't create a value in the output program at all. ----
1809 if (MI->isMetaInstruction() && MI->peekDebugInstrNum()) 0
1810 report("Metadata instruction should not have a value tracking number", MI); 0
1811 ----
1812 // Check the MachineMemOperands for basic consistency. ----
1813 for (MachineMemOperand *Op : MI->memoperands()) { 0
1814 if (Op->isLoad() && !MI->mayLoad()) 0
1815 report("Missing mayLoad flag", MI); 0
1816 if (Op->isStore() && !MI->mayStore()) 0
1817 report("Missing mayStore flag", MI); 0
1818 } ----
1819 ----
1820 // Debug values must not have a slot index. ----
1821 // Other instructions must have one, unless they are inside a bundle. ----
1822 if (LiveInts) { 0
1823 bool mapped = !LiveInts->isNotInMIMap(*MI); 0
1824 if (MI->isDebugOrPseudoInstr()) { 0
1825 if (mapped) 0
1826 report("Debug instruction has a slot index", MI); 0
1827 } else if (MI->isInsideBundle()) { 0
1828 if (mapped) 0
1829 report("Instruction inside bundle has a slot index", MI); 0
1830 } else { ----
1831 if (!mapped) 0
1832 report("Missing slot index", MI); 0
1833 } ----
1834 } ----
1835 ----
1836 unsigned Opc = MCID.getOpcode(); 0
1837 if (isPreISelGenericOpcode(Opc) || isPreISelGenericOptimizationHint(Opc)) { 0
1838 verifyPreISelGenericInstruction(MI); 0
1839 return; 0
1840 } ----
1841 ----
1842 StringRef ErrorInfo; 0
1843 if (!TII->verifyInstruction(*MI, ErrorInfo)) 0
1844 report(ErrorInfo.data(), MI); 0
1845 ----
1846 // Verify properties of various specific instruction types ----
1847 switch (MI->getOpcode()) { 0
1848 case TargetOpcode::COPY: { 0
1849 const MachineOperand &DstOp = MI->getOperand(0); 0
1850 const MachineOperand &SrcOp = MI->getOperand(1); 0
1851 const Register SrcReg = SrcOp.getReg(); 0
1852 const Register DstReg = DstOp.getReg(); 0
1853 ----
1854 LLT DstTy = MRI->getType(DstReg); 0
1855 LLT SrcTy = MRI->getType(SrcReg); 0
1856 if (SrcTy.isValid() && DstTy.isValid()) { 0
1857 // If both types are valid, check that the types are the same. ----
1858 if (SrcTy != DstTy) { 0
1859 report("Copy Instruction is illegal with mismatching types", MI); 0
1860 errs() << "Def = " << DstTy << ", Src = " << SrcTy << "\n"; 0
1861 } ----
1862 ----
1863 break; 0
1864 } ----
1865 ----
1866 if (!SrcTy.isValid() && !DstTy.isValid()) 0
1867 break; 0
1868 ----
1869 // If we have only one valid type, this is likely a copy between a virtual ----
1870 // and physical register. ----
1871 unsigned SrcSize = 0; 0
1872 unsigned DstSize = 0; 0
1873 if (SrcReg.isPhysical() && DstTy.isValid()) { 0
1874 const TargetRegisterClass *SrcRC = ----
1875 TRI->getMinimalPhysRegClassLLT(SrcReg, DstTy); 0
1876 if (SrcRC) 0
1877 SrcSize = TRI->getRegSizeInBits(*SrcRC); 0
1878 } ----
1879 ----
1880 if (SrcSize == 0) 0
1881 SrcSize = TRI->getRegSizeInBits(SrcReg, *MRI); 0
1882 ----
1883 if (DstReg.isPhysical() && SrcTy.isValid()) { 0
1884 const TargetRegisterClass *DstRC = ----
1885 TRI->getMinimalPhysRegClassLLT(DstReg, SrcTy); 0
1886 if (DstRC) 0
1887 DstSize = TRI->getRegSizeInBits(*DstRC); 0
1888 } ----
1889 ----
1890 if (DstSize == 0) 0
1891 DstSize = TRI->getRegSizeInBits(DstReg, *MRI); 0
1892 ----
1893 if (SrcSize != 0 && DstSize != 0 && SrcSize != DstSize) { 0
1894 if (!DstOp.getSubReg() && !SrcOp.getSubReg()) { 0
1895 report("Copy Instruction is illegal with mismatching sizes", MI); 0
1896 errs() << "Def Size = " << DstSize << ", Src Size = " << SrcSize 0
1897 << "\n"; 0
1898 } ----
1899 } ----
1900 break; 0
1901 } ----
1902 case TargetOpcode::STATEPOINT: { 0
1903 StatepointOpers SO(MI); 0
1904 if (!MI->getOperand(SO.getIDPos()).isImm() || 0
1905 !MI->getOperand(SO.getNBytesPos()).isImm() || 0
1906 !MI->getOperand(SO.getNCallArgsPos()).isImm()) { 0
1907 report("meta operands to STATEPOINT not constant!", MI); 0
1908 break; 0
1909 } ----
1910 ----
1911 auto VerifyStackMapConstant = [&](unsigned Offset) { 0
1912 if (Offset >= MI->getNumOperands()) { 0
1913 report("stack map constant to STATEPOINT is out of range!", MI); 0
1914 return; 0
1915 } ----
1916 if (!MI->getOperand(Offset - 1).isImm() || 0
1917 MI->getOperand(Offset - 1).getImm() != StackMaps::ConstantOp || 0
1918 !MI->getOperand(Offset).isImm()) 0
1919 report("stack map constant to STATEPOINT not well formed!", MI); 0
1920 }; 0
1921 VerifyStackMapConstant(SO.getCCIdx()); 0
1922 VerifyStackMapConstant(SO.getFlagsIdx()); 0
1923 VerifyStackMapConstant(SO.getNumDeoptArgsIdx()); 0
1924 VerifyStackMapConstant(SO.getNumGCPtrIdx()); 0
1925 VerifyStackMapConstant(SO.getNumAllocaIdx()); 0
1926 VerifyStackMapConstant(SO.getNumGcMapEntriesIdx()); 0
1927 ----
1928 // Verify that all explicit statepoint defs are tied to gc operands as ----
1929 // they are expected to be a relocation of gc operands. ----
1930 unsigned FirstGCPtrIdx = SO.getFirstGCPtrIdx(); 0
1931 unsigned LastGCPtrIdx = SO.getNumAllocaIdx() - 2; 0
1932 for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < MI->getNumDefs(); Idx++) { 0
1933 unsigned UseOpIdx; ----
1934 if (!MI->isRegTiedToUseOperand(Idx, &UseOpIdx)) { 0
1935 report("STATEPOINT defs expected to be tied", MI); 0
1936 break; 0
1937 } ----
1938 if (UseOpIdx < FirstGCPtrIdx || UseOpIdx > LastGCPtrIdx) { 0
1939 report("STATEPOINT def tied to non-gc operand", MI); 0
1940 break; 0
1941 } ----
1942 } ----
1943 ----
1944 // TODO: verify we have properly encoded deopt arguments ----
1945 } break; 0
1946 case TargetOpcode::INSERT_SUBREG: { 0
1947 unsigned InsertedSize; ----
1948 if (unsigned SubIdx = MI->getOperand(2).getSubReg()) 0
1949 InsertedSize = TRI->getSubRegIdxSize(SubIdx); 0
1950 else ----
1951 InsertedSize = TRI->getRegSizeInBits(MI->getOperand(2).getReg(), *MRI); 0
1952 unsigned SubRegSize = TRI->getSubRegIdxSize(MI->getOperand(3).getImm()); 0
1953 if (SubRegSize < InsertedSize) { 0
1954 report("INSERT_SUBREG expected inserted value to have equal or lesser " 0
1955 "size than the subreg it was inserted into", MI); ----
1956 break; 0
1957 } ----
1958 } break; 0
1959 case TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE: { 0
1960 unsigned NumOps = MI->getNumOperands(); 0
1961 if (!(NumOps & 1)) { 0
1962 report("Invalid number of operands for REG_SEQUENCE", MI); 0
1963 break; 0
1964 } ----
1965 ----
1966 for (unsigned I = 1; I != NumOps; I += 2) { 0
1967 const MachineOperand &RegOp = MI->getOperand(I); 0
1968 const MachineOperand &SubRegOp = MI->getOperand(I + 1); 0
1969 ----
1970 if (!RegOp.isReg()) 0
1971 report("Invalid register operand for REG_SEQUENCE", &RegOp, I); 0
1972 ----
1973 if (!SubRegOp.isImm() || SubRegOp.getImm() == 0 || 0
1974 SubRegOp.getImm() >= TRI->getNumSubRegIndices()) { 0
1975 report("Invalid subregister index operand for REG_SEQUENCE", 0
1976 &SubRegOp, I + 1); ----
1977 } ----
1978 } ----
1979 ----
1980 Register DstReg = MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1981 if (DstReg.isPhysical()) 0
1982 report("REG_SEQUENCE does not support physical register results", MI); 0
1983 ----
1984 if (MI->getOperand(0).getSubReg()) 0
1985 report("Invalid subreg result for REG_SEQUENCE", MI); 0
1986 ----
1987 break; 0
1988 } ----
1989 } ----
1990 } ----
1991 ----
1992 void ----
1993 MachineVerifier::visitMachineOperand(const MachineOperand *MO, unsigned MONum) { 0
1994 const MachineInstr *MI = MO->getParent(); 0
1995 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MI->getDesc(); 0
1996 unsigned NumDefs = MCID.getNumDefs(); 0
1997 if (MCID.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::PATCHPOINT) 0
1998 NumDefs = (MONum == 0 && MO->isReg()) ? NumDefs : 0; 0
1999 ----
2000 // The first MCID.NumDefs operands must be explicit register defines ----
2001 if (MONum < NumDefs) { 0
2002 const MCOperandInfo &MCOI = MCID.operands()[MONum]; 0
2003 if (!MO->isReg()) 0
2004 report("Explicit definition must be a register", MO, MONum); 0
2005 else if (!MO->isDef() && !MCOI.isOptionalDef()) 0
2006 report("Explicit definition marked as use", MO, MONum); 0
2007 else if (MO->isImplicit()) 0
2008 report("Explicit definition marked as implicit", MO, MONum); 0
2009 } else if (MONum < MCID.getNumOperands()) { 0
2010 const MCOperandInfo &MCOI = MCID.operands()[MONum]; 0
2011 // Don't check if it's the last operand in a variadic instruction. See, ----
2012 // e.g., LDM_RET in the arm back end. Check non-variadic operands only. ----
2013 bool IsOptional = MI->isVariadic() && MONum == MCID.getNumOperands() - 1; 0
2014 if (!IsOptional) { 0
2015 if (MO->isReg()) { 0
2016 if (MO->isDef() && !MCOI.isOptionalDef() && !MCID.variadicOpsAreDefs()) 0
2017 report("Explicit operand marked as def", MO, MONum); 0
2018 if (MO->isImplicit()) 0
2019 report("Explicit operand marked as implicit", MO, MONum); 0
2020 } ----
2021 ----
2022 // Check that an instruction has register operands only as expected. ----
2023 if (MCOI.OperandType == MCOI::OPERAND_REGISTER && 0
2024 !MO->isReg() && !MO->isFI()) 0
2025 report("Expected a register operand.", MO, MONum); 0
2026 if (MO->isReg()) { 0
2027 if (MCOI.OperandType == MCOI::OPERAND_IMMEDIATE || 0
2028 (MCOI.OperandType == MCOI::OPERAND_PCREL && 0
2029 !TII->isPCRelRegisterOperandLegal(*MO))) 0
2030 report("Expected a non-register operand.", MO, MONum); 0
2031 } ----
2032 } ----
2033 ----
2034 int TiedTo = MCID.getOperandConstraint(MONum, MCOI::TIED_TO); 0
2035 if (TiedTo != -1) { 0
2036 if (!MO->isReg()) 0
2037 report("Tied use must be a register", MO, MONum); 0
2038 else if (!MO->isTied()) 0
2039 report("Operand should be tied", MO, MONum); 0
2040 else if (unsigned(TiedTo) != MI->findTiedOperandIdx(MONum)) 0
2041 report("Tied def doesn't match MCInstrDesc", MO, MONum); 0
2042 else if (MO->getReg().isPhysical()) { 0
2043 const MachineOperand &MOTied = MI->getOperand(TiedTo); 0
2044 if (!MOTied.isReg()) 0
2045 report("Tied counterpart must be a register", &MOTied, TiedTo); 0
2046 else if (MOTied.getReg().isPhysical() && 0
2047 MO->getReg() != MOTied.getReg()) 0
2048 report("Tied physical registers must match.", &MOTied, TiedTo); 0
2049 } ----
2050 } else if (MO->isReg() && MO->isTied()) 0
2051 report("Explicit operand should not be tied", MO, MONum); 0
2052 } else { ----
2053 // ARM adds %reg0 operands to indicate predicates. We'll allow that. ----
2054 if (MO->isReg() && !MO->isImplicit() && !MI->isVariadic() && MO->getReg()) 0
2055 report("Extra explicit operand on non-variadic instruction", MO, MONum); 0
2056 } ----
2057 ----
2058 switch (MO->getType()) { 0
2059 case MachineOperand::MO_Register: { 0
2060 // Verify debug flag on debug instructions. Check this first because reg0 ----
2061 // indicates an undefined debug value. ----
2062 if (MI->isDebugInstr() && MO->isUse()) { 0
2063 if (!MO->isDebug()) 0
2064 report("Register operand must be marked debug", MO, MONum); 0
2065 } else if (MO->isDebug()) { 0
2066 report("Register operand must not be marked debug", MO, MONum); 0
2067 } ----
2068 ----
2069 const Register Reg = MO->getReg(); 0
2070 if (!Reg) 0
2071 return; 0
2072 if (MRI->tracksLiveness() && !MI->isDebugInstr()) 0
2073 checkLiveness(MO, MONum); 0
2074 ----
2075 if (MO->isDef() && MO->isUndef() && !MO->getSubReg() && 0
2076 MO->getReg().isVirtual()) // TODO: Apply to physregs too 0
2077 report("Undef virtual register def operands require a subregister", MO, MONum); 0
2078 ----
2079 // Verify the consistency of tied operands. ----
2080 if (MO->isTied()) { 0
2081 unsigned OtherIdx = MI->findTiedOperandIdx(MONum); 0
2082 const MachineOperand &OtherMO = MI->getOperand(OtherIdx); 0
2083 if (!OtherMO.isReg()) 0
2084 report("Must be tied to a register", MO, MONum); 0
2085 if (!OtherMO.isTied()) 0
2086 report("Missing tie flags on tied operand", MO, MONum); 0
2087 if (MI->findTiedOperandIdx(OtherIdx) != MONum) 0
2088 report("Inconsistent tie links", MO, MONum); 0
2089 if (MONum < MCID.getNumDefs()) { 0
2090 if (OtherIdx < MCID.getNumOperands()) { 0
2091 if (-1 == MCID.getOperandConstraint(OtherIdx, MCOI::TIED_TO)) 0
2092 report("Explicit def tied to explicit use without tie constraint", 0
2093 MO, MONum); ----
2094 } else { ----
2095 if (!OtherMO.isImplicit()) 0
2096 report("Explicit def should be tied to implicit use", MO, MONum); 0
2097 } ----
2098 } ----
2099 } ----
2100 ----
2101 // Verify two-address constraints after the twoaddressinstruction pass. ----
2102 // Both twoaddressinstruction pass and phi-node-elimination pass call ----
2103 // MRI->leaveSSA() to set MF as NoSSA, we should do the verification after ----
2104 // twoaddressinstruction pass not after phi-node-elimination pass. So we ----
2105 // shouldn't use the NoSSA as the condition, we should based on ----
2106 // TiedOpsRewritten property to verify two-address constraints, this ----
2107 // property will be set in twoaddressinstruction pass. ----
2108 unsigned DefIdx; ----
2109 if (MF->getProperties().hasProperty( 0
2110 MachineFunctionProperties::Property::TiedOpsRewritten) && 0
2111 MO->isUse() && MI->isRegTiedToDefOperand(MONum, &DefIdx) && 0
2112 Reg != MI->getOperand(DefIdx).getReg()) 0
2113 report("Two-address instruction operands must be identical", MO, MONum); 0
2114 ----
2115 // Check register classes. ----
2116 unsigned SubIdx = MO->getSubReg(); 0
2117 ----
2118 if (Reg.isPhysical()) { 0
2119 if (SubIdx) { 0
2120 report("Illegal subregister index for physical register", MO, MONum); 0
2121 return; 0
2122 } ----
2123 if (MONum < MCID.getNumOperands()) { 0
2124 if (const TargetRegisterClass *DRC = 0
2125 TII->getRegClass(MCID, MONum, TRI, *MF)) { 0
2126 if (!DRC->contains(Reg)) { 0
2127 report("Illegal physical register for instruction", MO, MONum); 0
2128 errs() << printReg(Reg, TRI) << " is not a " 0
2129 << TRI->getRegClassName(DRC) << " register.\n"; 0
2130 } ----
2131 } ----
2132 } ----
2133 if (MO->isRenamable()) { 0
2134 if (MRI->isReserved(Reg)) { 0
2135 report("isRenamable set on reserved register", MO, MONum); 0
2136 return; 0
2137 } ----
2138 } ----
2139 } else { ----
2140 // Virtual register. ----
2141 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI->getRegClassOrNull(Reg); 0
2142 if (!RC) { 0
2143 // This is a generic virtual register. ----
2144 ----
2145 // Do not allow undef uses for generic virtual registers. This ensures ----
2146 // getVRegDef can never fail and return null on a generic register. ----
2147 // ----
2148 // FIXME: This restriction should probably be broadened to all SSA ----
2149 // MIR. However, DetectDeadLanes/ProcessImplicitDefs technically still ----
2150 // run on the SSA function just before phi elimination. ----
2151 if (MO->isUndef()) 0
2152 report("Generic virtual register use cannot be undef", MO, MONum); 0
2153 ----
2154 // Debug value instruction is permitted to use undefined vregs. ----
2155 // This is a performance measure to skip the overhead of immediately ----
2156 // pruning unused debug operands. The final undef substitution occurs ----
2157 // when debug values are allocated in LDVImpl::handleDebugValue, so ----
2158 // these verifications always apply after this pass. ----
2159 if (isFunctionTracksDebugUserValues || !MO->isUse() || 0
2160 !MI->isDebugValue() || !MRI->def_empty(Reg)) { 0
2161 // If we're post-Select, we can't have gvregs anymore. ----
2162 if (isFunctionSelected) { 0
2163 report("Generic virtual register invalid in a Selected function", 0
2164 MO, MONum); ----
2165 return; 0
2166 } ----
2167 ----
2168 // The gvreg must have a type and it must not have a SubIdx. ----
2169 LLT Ty = MRI->getType(Reg); 0
2170 if (!Ty.isValid()) { 0
2171 report("Generic virtual register must have a valid type", MO, 0
2172 MONum); ----
2173 return; 0
2174 } ----
2175 ----
2176 const RegisterBank *RegBank = MRI->getRegBankOrNull(Reg); 0
2177 const RegisterBankInfo *RBI = MF->getSubtarget().getRegBankInfo(); 0
2178 ----
2179 // If we're post-RegBankSelect, the gvreg must have a bank. ----
2180 if (!RegBank && isFunctionRegBankSelected) { 0
2181 report("Generic virtual register must have a bank in a " 0
2182 "RegBankSelected function", ----
2183 MO, MONum); ----
2184 return; 0
2185 } ----
2186 ----
2187 // Make sure the register fits into its register bank if any. ----
2188 if (RegBank && Ty.isValid() && 0
2189 RBI->getMaximumSize(RegBank->getID()) < Ty.getSizeInBits()) { 0
2190 report("Register bank is too small for virtual register", MO, 0
2191 MONum); ----
2192 errs() << "Register bank " << RegBank->getName() << " too small(" 0
2193 << RBI->getMaximumSize(RegBank->getID()) << ") to fit " 0
2194 << Ty.getSizeInBits() << "-bits\n"; 0
2195 return; 0
2196 } ----
2197 } ----
2198 ----
2199 if (SubIdx) { 0
2200 report("Generic virtual register does not allow subregister index", MO, 0
2201 MONum); ----
2202 return; 0
2203 } ----
2204 ----
2205 // If this is a target specific instruction and this operand ----
2206 // has register class constraint, the virtual register must ----
2207 // comply to it. ----
2208 if (!isPreISelGenericOpcode(MCID.getOpcode()) && 0
2209 MONum < MCID.getNumOperands() && 0
2210 TII->getRegClass(MCID, MONum, TRI, *MF)) { 0
2211 report("Virtual register does not match instruction constraint", MO, 0
2212 MONum); ----
2213 errs() << "Expect register class " 0
2214 << TRI->getRegClassName( 0
2215 TII->getRegClass(MCID, MONum, TRI, *MF)) 0
2216 << " but got nothing\n"; 0
2217 return; 0
2218 } ----
2219 ----
2220 break; 0
2221 } ----
2222 if (SubIdx) { 0
2223 const TargetRegisterClass *SRC = ----
2224 TRI->getSubClassWithSubReg(RC, SubIdx); 0
2225 if (!SRC) { 0
2226 report("Invalid subregister index for virtual register", MO, MONum); 0
2227 errs() << "Register class " << TRI->getRegClassName(RC) 0
2228 << " does not support subreg index " << SubIdx << "\n"; 0
2229 return; 0
2230 } ----
2231 if (RC != SRC) { 0
2232 report("Invalid register class for subregister index", MO, MONum); 0
2233 errs() << "Register class " << TRI->getRegClassName(RC) 0
2234 << " does not fully support subreg index " << SubIdx << "\n"; 0
2235 return; 0
2236 } ----
2237 } ----
2238 if (MONum < MCID.getNumOperands()) { 0
2239 if (const TargetRegisterClass *DRC = 0
2240 TII->getRegClass(MCID, MONum, TRI, *MF)) { 0
2241 if (SubIdx) { 0
2242 const TargetRegisterClass *SuperRC = ----
2243 TRI->getLargestLegalSuperClass(RC, *MF); 0
2244 if (!SuperRC) { 0
2245 report("No largest legal super class exists.", MO, MONum); 0
2246 return; 0
2247 } ----
2248 DRC = TRI->getMatchingSuperRegClass(SuperRC, DRC, SubIdx); 0
2249 if (!DRC) { 0
2250 report("No matching super-reg register class.", MO, MONum); 0
2251 return; 0
2252 } ----
2253 } ----
2254 if (!RC->hasSuperClassEq(DRC)) { 0
2255 report("Illegal virtual register for instruction", MO, MONum); 0
2256 errs() << "Expected a " << TRI->getRegClassName(DRC) 0
2257 << " register, but got a " << TRI->getRegClassName(RC) 0
2258 << " register\n"; 0
2259 } ----
2260 } ----
2261 } ----
2262 } ----
2263 break; 0
2264 } ----
2265 ----
2266 case MachineOperand::MO_RegisterMask: 0
2267 regMasks.push_back(MO->getRegMask()); 0
2268 break; 0
2269 ----
2270 case MachineOperand::MO_MachineBasicBlock: 0
2271 if (MI->isPHI() && !MO->getMBB()->isSuccessor(MI->getParent())) 0
2272 report("PHI operand is not in the CFG", MO, MONum); 0
2273 break; 0
2274 ----
2275 case MachineOperand::MO_FrameIndex: 0
2276 if (LiveStks && LiveStks->hasInterval(MO->getIndex()) && 0
2277 LiveInts && !LiveInts->isNotInMIMap(*MI)) { 0
2278 int FI = MO->getIndex(); 0
2279 LiveInterval &LI = LiveStks->getInterval(FI); 0
2280 SlotIndex Idx = LiveInts->getInstructionIndex(*MI); 0
2281 ----
2282 bool stores = MI->mayStore(); 0
2283 bool loads = MI->mayLoad(); 0
2284 // For a memory-to-memory move, we need to check if the frame ----
2285 // index is used for storing or loading, by inspecting the ----
2286 // memory operands. ----
2287 if (stores && loads) { 0
2288 for (auto *MMO : MI->memoperands()) { 0
2289 const PseudoSourceValue *PSV = MMO->getPseudoValue(); 0
2290 if (PSV == nullptr) continue; 0
2291 const FixedStackPseudoSourceValue *Value = ----
2292 dyn_cast(PSV); 0
2293 if (Value == nullptr) continue; 0
2294 if (Value->getFrameIndex() != FI) continue; 0
2295 ----
2296 if (MMO->isStore()) 0
2297 loads = false; 0
2298 else ----
2299 stores = false; 0
2300 break; 0
2301 } ----
2302 if (loads == stores) 0
2303 report("Missing fixed stack memoperand.", MI); 0
2304 } ----
2305 if (loads && !LI.liveAt(Idx.getRegSlot(true))) { 0
2306 report("Instruction loads from dead spill slot", MO, MONum); 0
2307 errs() << "Live stack: " << LI << '\n'; 0
2308 } ----
2309 if (stores && !LI.liveAt(Idx.getRegSlot())) { 0
2310 report("Instruction stores to dead spill slot", MO, MONum); 0
2311 errs() << "Live stack: " << LI << '\n'; 0
2312 } ----
2313 } ----
2314 break; 0
2315 ----
2316 case MachineOperand::MO_CFIIndex: 0
2317 if (MO->getCFIIndex() >= MF->getFrameInstructions().size()) 0
2318 report("CFI instruction has invalid index", MO, MONum); 0
2319 break; 0
2320 ----
2321 default: 0
2322 break; 0
2323 } ----
2324 } ----
2325 ----
2326 void MachineVerifier::checkLivenessAtUse(const MachineOperand *MO, 0
2327 unsigned MONum, SlotIndex UseIdx, ----
2328 const LiveRange &LR, ----
2329 Register VRegOrUnit, ----
2330 LaneBitmask LaneMask) { ----
2331 LiveQueryResult LRQ = LR.Query(UseIdx); 0
2332 // Check if we have a segment at the use, note however that we only need one ----
2333 // live subregister range, the others may be dead. ----
2334 if (!LRQ.valueIn() && LaneMask.none()) { 0
2335 report("No live segment at use", MO, MONum); 0
2336 report_context_liverange(LR); 0
2337 report_context_vreg_regunit(VRegOrUnit); 0
2338 report_context(UseIdx); 0
2339 } ----
2340 if (MO->isKill() && !LRQ.isKill()) { 0
2341 report("Live range continues after kill flag", MO, MONum); 0
2342 report_context_liverange(LR); 0
2343 report_context_vreg_regunit(VRegOrUnit); 0
2344 if (LaneMask.any()) 0
2345 report_context_lanemask(LaneMask); 0
2346 report_context(UseIdx); 0
2347 } ----
2348 } 0
2349 ----
2350 void MachineVerifier::checkLivenessAtDef(const MachineOperand *MO, 0
2351 unsigned MONum, SlotIndex DefIdx, ----
2352 const LiveRange &LR, ----
2353 Register VRegOrUnit, ----
2354 bool SubRangeCheck, ----
2355 LaneBitmask LaneMask) { ----
2356 if (const VNInfo *VNI = LR.getVNInfoAt(DefIdx)) { 0
2357 // The LR can correspond to the whole reg and its def slot is not obliged ----
2358 // to be the same as the MO' def slot. E.g. when we check here "normal" ----
2359 // subreg MO but there is other EC subreg MO in the same instruction so the ----
2360 // whole reg has EC def slot and differs from the currently checked MO' def ----
2361 // slot. For example: ----
2362 // %0 [16e,32r:0) 0@16e L..3 [16e,32r:0) 0@16e L..C [16r,32r:0) 0@16r ----
2363 // Check that there is an early-clobber def of the same superregister ----
2364 // somewhere is performed in visitMachineFunctionAfter() ----
2365 if (((SubRangeCheck || MO->getSubReg() == 0) && VNI->def != DefIdx) || 0
2366 !SlotIndex::isSameInstr(VNI->def, DefIdx) || 0
2367 (VNI->def != DefIdx && 0
2368 (!VNI->def.isEarlyClobber() || !DefIdx.isRegister()))) { 0
2369 report("Inconsistent valno->def", MO, MONum); 0
2370 report_context_liverange(LR); 0
2371 report_context_vreg_regunit(VRegOrUnit); 0
2372 if (LaneMask.any()) 0
2373 report_context_lanemask(LaneMask); 0
2374 report_context(*VNI); 0
2375 report_context(DefIdx); 0
2376 } ----
2377 } else { ----
2378 report("No live segment at def", MO, MONum); 0
2379 report_context_liverange(LR); 0
2380 report_context_vreg_regunit(VRegOrUnit); 0
2381 if (LaneMask.any()) 0
2382 report_context_lanemask(LaneMask); 0
2383 report_context(DefIdx); 0
2384 } ----
2385 // Check that, if the dead def flag is present, LiveInts agree. ----
2386 if (MO->isDead()) { 0
2387 LiveQueryResult LRQ = LR.Query(DefIdx); 0
2388 if (!LRQ.isDeadDef()) { 0
2389 assert(VRegOrUnit.isVirtual() && "Expecting a virtual register."); 0
2390 // A dead subreg def only tells us that the specific subreg is dead. There ----
2391 // could be other non-dead defs of other subregs, or we could have other ----
2392 // parts of the register being live through the instruction. So unless we ----
2393 // are checking liveness for a subrange it is ok for the live range to ----
2394 // continue, given that we have a dead def of a subregister. ----
2395 if (SubRangeCheck || MO->getSubReg() == 0) { 0
2396 report("Live range continues after dead def flag", MO, MONum); 0
2397 report_context_liverange(LR); 0
2398 report_context_vreg_regunit(VRegOrUnit); 0
2399 if (LaneMask.any()) 0
2400 report_context_lanemask(LaneMask); 0
2401 } ----
2402 } ----
2403 } ----
2404 } 0
2405 ----
2406 void MachineVerifier::checkLiveness(const MachineOperand *MO, unsigned MONum) { 0
2407 const MachineInstr *MI = MO->getParent(); 0
2408 const Register Reg = MO->getReg(); 0
2409 const unsigned SubRegIdx = MO->getSubReg(); 0
2410 ----
2411 const LiveInterval *LI = nullptr; 0
2412 if (LiveInts && Reg.isVirtual()) { 0
2413 if (LiveInts->hasInterval(Reg)) { 0
2414 LI = &LiveInts->getInterval(Reg); 0
2415 if (SubRegIdx != 0 && (MO->isDef() || !MO->isUndef()) && !LI->empty() && 0
2416 !LI->hasSubRanges() && MRI->shouldTrackSubRegLiveness(Reg)) 0
2417 report("Live interval for subreg operand has no subranges", MO, MONum); 0
2418 } else { ----
2419 report("Virtual register has no live interval", MO, MONum); 0
2420 } ----
2421 } ----
2422 ----
2423 // Both use and def operands can read a register. ----
2424 if (MO->readsReg()) { 0
2425 if (MO->isKill()) 0
2426 addRegWithSubRegs(regsKilled, Reg); 0
2427 ----
2428 // Check that LiveVars knows this kill (unless we are inside a bundle, in ----
2429 // which case we have already checked that LiveVars knows any kills on the ----
2430 // bundle header instead). ----
2431 if (LiveVars && Reg.isVirtual() && MO->isKill() && 0
2432 !MI->isBundledWithPred()) { 0
2433 LiveVariables::VarInfo &VI = LiveVars->getVarInfo(Reg); 0
2434 if (!is_contained(VI.Kills, MI)) 0
2435 report("Kill missing from LiveVariables", MO, MONum); 0
2436 } ----
2437 ----
2438 // Check LiveInts liveness and kill. ----
2439 if (LiveInts && !LiveInts->isNotInMIMap(*MI)) { 0
2440 SlotIndex UseIdx = LiveInts->getInstructionIndex(*MI); 0
2441 // Check the cached regunit intervals. ----
2442 if (Reg.isPhysical() && !isReserved(Reg)) { 0
2443 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI->regunits(Reg.asMCReg())) { 0
2444 if (MRI->isReservedRegUnit(Unit)) 0
2445 continue; 0
2446 if (const LiveRange *LR = LiveInts->getCachedRegUnit(Unit)) 0
2447 checkLivenessAtUse(MO, MONum, UseIdx, *LR, Unit); 0
2448 } ----
2449 } ----
2450 ----
2451 if (Reg.isVirtual()) { 0
2452 // This is a virtual register interval. ----
2453 checkLivenessAtUse(MO, MONum, UseIdx, *LI, Reg); 0
2454 ----
2455 if (LI->hasSubRanges() && !MO->isDef()) { 0
2456 LaneBitmask MOMask = SubRegIdx != 0 ----
2457 ? TRI->getSubRegIndexLaneMask(SubRegIdx) 0
2458 : MRI->getMaxLaneMaskForVReg(Reg); 0
2459 LaneBitmask LiveInMask; 0
2460 for (const LiveInterval::SubRange &SR : LI->subranges()) { 0
2461 if ((MOMask & SR.LaneMask).none()) 0
2462 continue; 0
2463 checkLivenessAtUse(MO, MONum, UseIdx, SR, Reg, SR.LaneMask); 0
2464 LiveQueryResult LRQ = SR.Query(UseIdx); 0
2465 if (LRQ.valueIn()) 0
2466 LiveInMask |= SR.LaneMask; 0
2467 } ----
2468 // At least parts of the register has to be live at the use. ----
2469 if ((LiveInMask & MOMask).none()) { 0
2470 report("No live subrange at use", MO, MONum); 0
2471 report_context(*LI); 0
2472 report_context(UseIdx); 0
2473 } ----
2474 } ----
2475 } ----
2476 } ----
2477 ----
2478 // Use of a dead register. ----
2479 if (!regsLive.count(Reg)) { 0
2480 if (Reg.isPhysical()) { 0
2481 // Reserved registers may be used even when 'dead'. ----
2482 bool Bad = !isReserved(Reg); 0
2483 // We are fine if just any subregister has a defined value. ----
2484 if (Bad) { 0
2485 ----
2486 for (const MCPhysReg &SubReg : TRI->subregs(Reg)) { 0
2487 if (regsLive.count(SubReg)) { 0
2488 Bad = false; 0
2489 break; 0
2490 } ----
2491 } ----
2492 } ----
2493 // If there is an additional implicit-use of a super register we stop ----
2494 // here. By definition we are fine if the super register is not ----
2495 // (completely) dead, if the complete super register is dead we will ----
2496 // get a report for its operand. ----
2497 if (Bad) { 0
2498 for (const MachineOperand &MOP : MI->uses()) { 0
2499 if (!MOP.isReg() || !MOP.isImplicit()) 0
2500 continue; 0
2501 ----
2502 if (!MOP.getReg().isPhysical()) 0
2503 continue; 0
2504 ----
2505 if (llvm::is_contained(TRI->subregs(MOP.getReg()), Reg)) 0
2506 Bad = false; 0
2507 } ----
2508 } ----
2509 if (Bad) 0
2510 report("Using an undefined physical register", MO, MONum); 0
2511 } else if (MRI->def_empty(Reg)) { 0
2512 report("Reading virtual register without a def", MO, MONum); 0
2513 } else { ----
2514 BBInfo &MInfo = MBBInfoMap[MI->getParent()]; 0
2515 // We don't know which virtual registers are live in, so only complain ----
2516 // if vreg was killed in this MBB. Otherwise keep track of vregs that ----
2517 // must be live in. PHI instructions are handled separately. ----
2518 if (MInfo.regsKilled.count(Reg)) 0
2519 report("Using a killed virtual register", MO, MONum); 0
2520 else if (!MI->isPHI()) 0
2521 MInfo.vregsLiveIn.insert(std::make_pair(Reg, MI)); 0
2522 } ----
2523 } ----
2524 } ----
2525 ----
2526 if (MO->isDef()) { 0
2527 // Register defined. ----
2528 // TODO: verify that earlyclobber ops are not used. ----
2529 if (MO->isDead()) 0
2530 addRegWithSubRegs(regsDead, Reg); 0
2531 else ----
2532 addRegWithSubRegs(regsDefined, Reg); 0
2533 ----
2534 // Verify SSA form. ----
2535 if (MRI->isSSA() && Reg.isVirtual() && 0
2536 std::next(MRI->def_begin(Reg)) != MRI->def_end()) 0
2537 report("Multiple virtual register defs in SSA form", MO, MONum); 0
2538 ----
2539 // Check LiveInts for a live segment, but only for virtual registers. ----
2540 if (LiveInts && !LiveInts->isNotInMIMap(*MI)) { 0
2541 SlotIndex DefIdx = LiveInts->getInstructionIndex(*MI); 0
2542 DefIdx = DefIdx.getRegSlot(MO->isEarlyClobber()); 0
2543 ----
2544 if (Reg.isVirtual()) { 0
2545 checkLivenessAtDef(MO, MONum, DefIdx, *LI, Reg); 0
2546 ----
2547 if (LI->hasSubRanges()) { 0
2548 LaneBitmask MOMask = SubRegIdx != 0 ----
2549 ? TRI->getSubRegIndexLaneMask(SubRegIdx) 0
2550 : MRI->getMaxLaneMaskForVReg(Reg); 0
2551 for (const LiveInterval::SubRange &SR : LI->subranges()) { 0
2552 if ((SR.LaneMask & MOMask).none()) 0
2553 continue; 0
2554 checkLivenessAtDef(MO, MONum, DefIdx, SR, Reg, true, SR.LaneMask); 0
2555 } ----
2556 } ----
2557 } ----
2558 } ----
2559 } ----
2560 } 0
2561 ----
2562 // This function gets called after visiting all instructions in a bundle. The ----
2563 // argument points to the bundle header. ----
2564 // Normal stand-alone instructions are also considered 'bundles', and this ----
2565 // function is called for all of them. ----
2566 void MachineVerifier::visitMachineBundleAfter(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
2567 BBInfo &MInfo = MBBInfoMap[MI->getParent()]; 0
2568 set_union(MInfo.regsKilled, regsKilled); 0
2569 set_subtract(regsLive, regsKilled); regsKilled.clear(); 0
2570 // Kill any masked registers. ----
2571 while (!regMasks.empty()) { 0
2572 const uint32_t *Mask = regMasks.pop_back_val(); 0
2573 for (Register Reg : regsLive) 0
2574 if (Reg.isPhysical() && 0
2575 MachineOperand::clobbersPhysReg(Mask, Reg.asMCReg())) 0
2576 regsDead.push_back(Reg); 0
2577 } ----
2578 set_subtract(regsLive, regsDead); regsDead.clear(); 0
2579 set_union(regsLive, regsDefined); regsDefined.clear(); 0
2580 } 0
2581 ----
2582 void ----
2583 MachineVerifier::visitMachineBasicBlockAfter(const MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
2584 MBBInfoMap[MBB].regsLiveOut = regsLive; 0
2585 regsLive.clear(); 0
2586 ----
2587 if (Indexes) { 0
2588 SlotIndex stop = Indexes->getMBBEndIdx(MBB); 0
2589 if (!(stop > lastIndex)) { 0
2590 report("Block ends before last instruction index", MBB); 0
2591 errs() << "Block ends at " << stop 0
2592 << " last instruction was at " << lastIndex << '\n'; 0
2593 } ----
2594 lastIndex = stop; 0
2595 } ----
2596 } 0
2597 ----
2598 namespace { ----
2599 // This implements a set of registers that serves as a filter: can filter other ----
2600 // sets by passing through elements not in the filter and blocking those that ----
2601 // are. Any filter implicitly includes the full set of physical registers upon ----
2602 // creation, thus filtering them all out. The filter itself as a set only grows, ----
2603 // and needs to be as efficient as possible. ----
2604 struct VRegFilter { ----
2605 // Add elements to the filter itself. \pre Input set \p FromRegSet must have ----
2606 // no duplicates. Both virtual and physical registers are fine. ----
2607 template void add(const RegSetT &FromRegSet) { 0
2608 SmallVector VRegsBuffer; 0
2609 filterAndAdd(FromRegSet, VRegsBuffer); 0
2610 } 0
2611 // Filter \p FromRegSet through the filter and append passed elements into \p ----
2612 // ToVRegs. All elements appended are then added to the filter itself. ----
2613 // \returns true if anything changed. ----
2614 template ----
2615 bool filterAndAdd(const RegSetT &FromRegSet, 0
2616 SmallVectorImpl &ToVRegs) { ----
2617 unsigned SparseUniverse = Sparse.size(); 0
2618 unsigned NewSparseUniverse = SparseUniverse; 0
2619 unsigned NewDenseSize = Dense.size(); 0
2620 size_t Begin = ToVRegs.size(); 0
2621 for (Register Reg : FromRegSet) { 0
2622 if (!Reg.isVirtual()) 0
2623 continue; 0
2624 unsigned Index = Register::virtReg2Index(Reg); 0
2625 if (Index < SparseUniverseMax) { 0
2626 if (Index < SparseUniverse && Sparse.test(Index)) 0
2627 continue; 0
2628 NewSparseUniverse = std::max(NewSparseUniverse, Index + 1); 0
2629 } else { ----
2630 if (Dense.count(Reg)) 0
2631 continue; 0
2632 ++NewDenseSize; 0
2633 } ----
2634 ToVRegs.push_back(Reg); 0
2635 } ----
2636 size_t End = ToVRegs.size(); 0
2637 if (Begin == End) 0
2638 return false; 0
2639 // Reserving space in sets once performs better than doing so continuously ----
2640 // and pays easily for double look-ups (even in Dense with SparseUniverseMax ----
2641 // tuned all the way down) and double iteration (the second one is over a ----
2642 // SmallVector, which is a lot cheaper compared to DenseSet or BitVector). ----
2643 Sparse.resize(NewSparseUniverse); 0
2644 Dense.reserve(NewDenseSize); 0
2645 for (unsigned I = Begin; I < End; ++I) { 0
2646 Register Reg = ToVRegs[I]; 0
2647 unsigned Index = Register::virtReg2Index(Reg); 0
2648 if (Index < SparseUniverseMax) 0
2649 Sparse.set(Index); 0
2650 else ----
2651 Dense.insert(Reg); 0
2652 } ----
2653 return true; 0
2654 } ----
2655 ----
2656 private: ----
2657 static constexpr unsigned SparseUniverseMax = 10 * 1024 * 8; ----
2658 // VRegs indexed within SparseUniverseMax are tracked by Sparse, those beyound ----
2659 // are tracked by Dense. The only purpose of the threashold and the Dense set ----
2660 // is to have a reasonably growing memory usage in pathological cases (large ----
2661 // number of very sparse VRegFilter instances live at the same time). In ----
2662 // practice even in the worst-by-execution time cases having all elements ----
2663 // tracked by Sparse (very large SparseUniverseMax scenario) tends to be more ----
2664 // space efficient than if tracked by Dense. The threashold is set to keep the ----
2665 // worst-case memory usage within 2x of figures determined empirically for ----
2666 // "all Dense" scenario in such worst-by-execution-time cases. ----
2667 BitVector Sparse; ----
2668 DenseSet Dense; ----
2669 }; ----
2670 ----
2671 // Implements both a transfer function and a (binary, in-place) join operator ----
2672 // for a dataflow over register sets with set union join and filtering transfer ----
2673 // (out_b = in_b \ filter_b). filter_b is expected to be set-up ahead of time. ----
2674 // Maintains out_b as its state, allowing for O(n) iteration over it at any ----
2675 // time, where n is the size of the set (as opposed to O(U) where U is the ----
2676 // universe). filter_b implicitly contains all physical registers at all times. ----
2677 class FilteringVRegSet { ----
2678 VRegFilter Filter; ----
2679 SmallVector VRegs; ----
2680 ----
2681 public: ----
2682 // Set-up the filter_b. \pre Input register set \p RS must have no duplicates. ----
2683 // Both virtual and physical registers are fine. ----
2684 template void addToFilter(const RegSetT &RS) { 0
2685 Filter.add(RS); 0
2686 } 0
2687 // Passes \p RS through the filter_b (transfer function) and adds what's left ----
2688 // to itself (out_b). ----
2689 template bool add(const RegSetT &RS) { 0
2690 // Double-duty the Filter: to maintain VRegs a set (and the join operation ----
2691 // a set union) just add everything being added here to the Filter as well. ----
2692 return Filter.filterAndAdd(RS, VRegs); 0
2693 } ----
2694 using const_iterator = decltype(VRegs)::const_iterator; ----
2695 const_iterator begin() const { return VRegs.begin(); } 0
2696 const_iterator end() const { return VRegs.end(); } 0
2697 size_t size() const { return VRegs.size(); } 0
2698 }; ----
2699 } // namespace ----
2700 ----
2701 // Calculate the largest possible vregsPassed sets. These are the registers that ----
2702 // can pass through an MBB live, but may not be live every time. It is assumed ----
2703 // that all vregsPassed sets are empty before the call. ----
2704 void MachineVerifier::calcRegsPassed() { 0
2705 if (MF->empty()) 0
2706 // ReversePostOrderTraversal doesn't handle empty functions. ----
2707 return; 0
2708 ----
2709 for (const MachineBasicBlock *MB : 0
2710 ReversePostOrderTraversal(MF)) { 0
2711 FilteringVRegSet VRegs; 0
2712 BBInfo &Info = MBBInfoMap[MB]; 0
2713 assert(Info.reachable); 0
2714 ----
2715 VRegs.addToFilter(Info.regsKilled); 0
2716 VRegs.addToFilter(Info.regsLiveOut); 0
2717 for (const MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MB->predecessors()) { 0
2718 const BBInfo &PredInfo = MBBInfoMap[Pred]; 0
2719 if (!PredInfo.reachable) 0
2720 continue; 0
2721 ----
2722 VRegs.add(PredInfo.regsLiveOut); 0
2723 VRegs.add(PredInfo.vregsPassed); 0
2724 } ----
2725 Info.vregsPassed.reserve(VRegs.size()); 0
2726 Info.vregsPassed.insert(VRegs.begin(), VRegs.end()); 0
2727 } 0
2728 } ----
2729 ----
2730 // Calculate the set of virtual registers that must be passed through each basic ----
2731 // block in order to satisfy the requirements of successor blocks. This is very ----
2732 // similar to calcRegsPassed, only backwards. ----
2733 void MachineVerifier::calcRegsRequired() { 0
2734 // First push live-in regs to predecessors' vregsRequired. ----
2735 SmallPtrSet todo; 0
2736 for (const auto &MBB : *MF) { 0
2737 BBInfo &MInfo = MBBInfoMap[&MBB]; 0
2738 for (const MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB.predecessors()) { 0
2739 BBInfo &PInfo = MBBInfoMap[Pred]; 0
2740 if (PInfo.addRequired(MInfo.vregsLiveIn)) 0
2741 todo.insert(Pred); 0
2742 } ----
2743 ----
2744 // Handle the PHI node. ----
2745 for (const MachineInstr &MI : MBB.phis()) { 0
2746 for (unsigned i = 1, e = MI.getNumOperands(); i != e; i += 2) { 0
2747 // Skip those Operands which are undef regs or not regs. ----
2748 if (!MI.getOperand(i).isReg() || !MI.getOperand(i).readsReg()) 0
2749 continue; 0
2750 ----
2751 // Get register and predecessor for one PHI edge. ----
2752 Register Reg = MI.getOperand(i).getReg(); 0
2753 const MachineBasicBlock *Pred = MI.getOperand(i + 1).getMBB(); 0
2754 ----
2755 BBInfo &PInfo = MBBInfoMap[Pred]; 0
2756 if (PInfo.addRequired(Reg)) 0
2757 todo.insert(Pred); 0
2758 } ----
2759 } ----
2760 } ----
2761 ----
2762 // Iteratively push vregsRequired to predecessors. This will converge to the ----
2763 // same final state regardless of DenseSet iteration order. ----
2764 while (!todo.empty()) { 0
2765 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB = *todo.begin(); 0
2766 todo.erase(MBB); 0
2767 BBInfo &MInfo = MBBInfoMap[MBB]; 0
2768 for (const MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB->predecessors()) { 0
2769 if (Pred == MBB) 0
2770 continue; 0
2771 BBInfo &SInfo = MBBInfoMap[Pred]; 0
2772 if (SInfo.addRequired(MInfo.vregsRequired)) 0
2773 todo.insert(Pred); 0
2774 } ----
2775 } ----
2776 } 0
2777 ----
2778 // Check PHI instructions at the beginning of MBB. It is assumed that ----
2779 // calcRegsPassed has been run so BBInfo::isLiveOut is valid. ----
2780 void MachineVerifier::checkPHIOps(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
2781 BBInfo &MInfo = MBBInfoMap[&MBB]; 0
2782 ----
2783 SmallPtrSet seen; 0
2784 for (const MachineInstr &Phi : MBB) { 0
2785 if (!Phi.isPHI()) 0
2786 break; 0
2787 seen.clear(); 0
2788 ----
2789 const MachineOperand &MODef = Phi.getOperand(0); 0
2790 if (!MODef.isReg() || !MODef.isDef()) { 0
2791 report("Expected first PHI operand to be a register def", &MODef, 0); 0
2792 continue; 0
2793 } ----
2794 if (MODef.isTied() || MODef.isImplicit() || MODef.isInternalRead() || 0
2795 MODef.isEarlyClobber() || MODef.isDebug()) 0
2796 report("Unexpected flag on PHI operand", &MODef, 0); 0
2797 Register DefReg = MODef.getReg(); 0
2798 if (!DefReg.isVirtual()) 0
2799 report("Expected first PHI operand to be a virtual register", &MODef, 0); 0
2800 ----
2801 for (unsigned I = 1, E = Phi.getNumOperands(); I != E; I += 2) { 0
2802 const MachineOperand &MO0 = Phi.getOperand(I); 0
2803 if (!MO0.isReg()) { 0
2804 report("Expected PHI operand to be a register", &MO0, I); 0
2805 continue; 0
2806 } ----
2807 if (MO0.isImplicit() || MO0.isInternalRead() || MO0.isEarlyClobber() || 0
2808 MO0.isDebug() || MO0.isTied()) 0
2809 report("Unexpected flag on PHI operand", &MO0, I); 0
2810 ----
2811 const MachineOperand &MO1 = Phi.getOperand(I + 1); 0
2812 if (!MO1.isMBB()) { 0
2813 report("Expected PHI operand to be a basic block", &MO1, I + 1); 0
2814 continue; 0
2815 } ----
2816 ----
2817 const MachineBasicBlock &Pre = *MO1.getMBB(); 0
2818 if (!Pre.isSuccessor(&MBB)) { 0
2819 report("PHI input is not a predecessor block", &MO1, I + 1); 0
2820 continue; 0
2821 } ----
2822 ----
2823 if (MInfo.reachable) { 0
2824 seen.insert(&Pre); 0
2825 BBInfo &PrInfo = MBBInfoMap[&Pre]; 0
2826 if (!MO0.isUndef() && PrInfo.reachable && 0
2827 !PrInfo.isLiveOut(MO0.getReg())) 0
2828 report("PHI operand is not live-out from predecessor", &MO0, I); 0
2829 } ----
2830 } ----
2831 ----
2832 // Did we see all predecessors? ----
2833 if (MInfo.reachable) { 0
2834 for (MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB.predecessors()) { 0
2835 if (!seen.count(Pred)) { 0
2836 report("Missing PHI operand", &Phi); 0
2837 errs() << printMBBReference(*Pred) 0
2838 << " is a predecessor according to the CFG.\n"; 0
2839 } ----
2840 } ----
2841 } ----
2842 } ----
2843 } 0
2844 ----
2845 void MachineVerifier::visitMachineFunctionAfter() { 0
2846 calcRegsPassed(); 0
2847 ----
2848 for (const MachineBasicBlock &MBB : *MF) 0
2849 checkPHIOps(MBB); 0
2850 ----
2851 // Now check liveness info if available ----
2852 calcRegsRequired(); 0
2853 ----
2854 // Check for killed virtual registers that should be live out. ----
2855 for (const auto &MBB : *MF) { 0
2856 BBInfo &MInfo = MBBInfoMap[&MBB]; 0
2857 for (Register VReg : MInfo.vregsRequired) 0
2858 if (MInfo.regsKilled.count(VReg)) { 0
2859 report("Virtual register killed in block, but needed live out.", &MBB); 0
2860 errs() << "Virtual register " << printReg(VReg) 0
2861 << " is used after the block.\n"; 0
2862 } ----
2863 } ----
2864 ----
2865 if (!MF->empty()) { 0
2866 BBInfo &MInfo = MBBInfoMap[&MF->front()]; 0
2867 for (Register VReg : MInfo.vregsRequired) { 0
2868 report("Virtual register defs don't dominate all uses.", MF); 0
2869 report_context_vreg(VReg); 0
2870 } ----
2871 } ----
2872 ----
2873 if (LiveVars) 0
2874 verifyLiveVariables(); 0
2875 if (LiveInts) 0
2876 verifyLiveIntervals(); 0
2877 ----
2878 // Check live-in list of each MBB. If a register is live into MBB, check ----
2879 // that the register is in regsLiveOut of each predecessor block. Since ----
2880 // this must come from a definition in the predecesssor or its live-in ----
2881 // list, this will catch a live-through case where the predecessor does not ----
2882 // have the register in its live-in list. This currently only checks ----
2883 // registers that have no aliases, are not allocatable and are not ----
2884 // reserved, which could mean a condition code register for instance. ----
2885 if (MRI->tracksLiveness()) 0
2886 for (const auto &MBB : *MF) 0
2887 for (MachineBasicBlock::RegisterMaskPair P : MBB.liveins()) { 0
2888 MCPhysReg LiveInReg = P.PhysReg; 0
2889 bool hasAliases = MCRegAliasIterator(LiveInReg, TRI, false).isValid(); 0
2890 if (hasAliases || isAllocatable(LiveInReg) || isReserved(LiveInReg)) 0
2891 continue; 0
2892 for (const MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB.predecessors()) { 0
2893 BBInfo &PInfo = MBBInfoMap[Pred]; 0
2894 if (!PInfo.regsLiveOut.count(LiveInReg)) { 0
2895 report("Live in register not found to be live out from predecessor.", 0
2896 &MBB); ----
2897 errs() << TRI->getName(LiveInReg) 0
2898 << " not found to be live out from " ----
2899 << printMBBReference(*Pred) << "\n"; 0
2900 } ----
2901 } ----
2902 } ----
2903 ----
2904 for (auto CSInfo : MF->getCallSitesInfo()) 0
2905 if (!CSInfo.first->isCall()) 0
2906 report("Call site info referencing instruction that is not call", MF); 0
2907 ----
2908 // If there's debug-info, check that we don't have any duplicate value ----
2909 // tracking numbers. ----
2910 if (MF->getFunction().getSubprogram()) { 0
2911 DenseSet SeenNumbers; 0
2912 for (const auto &MBB : *MF) { 0
2913 for (const auto &MI : MBB) { 0
2914 if (auto Num = MI.peekDebugInstrNum()) { 0
2915 auto Result = SeenNumbers.insert((unsigned)Num); 0
2916 if (!Result.second) 0
2917 report("Instruction has a duplicated value tracking number", &MI); 0
2918 } ----
2919 } ----
2920 } ----
2921 } 0
2922 } 0
2923 ----
2924 void MachineVerifier::verifyLiveVariables() { 0
2925 assert(LiveVars && "Don't call verifyLiveVariables without LiveVars"); 0
2926 for (unsigned I = 0, E = MRI->getNumVirtRegs(); I != E; ++I) { 0
2927 Register Reg = Register::index2VirtReg(I); 0
2928 LiveVariables::VarInfo &VI = LiveVars->getVarInfo(Reg); 0
2929 for (const auto &MBB : *MF) { 0
2930 BBInfo &MInfo = MBBInfoMap[&MBB]; 0
2931 ----
2932 // Our vregsRequired should be identical to LiveVariables' AliveBlocks ----
2933 if (MInfo.vregsRequired.count(Reg)) { 0
2934 if (!VI.AliveBlocks.test(MBB.getNumber())) { 0
2935 report("LiveVariables: Block missing from AliveBlocks", &MBB); 0
2936 errs() << "Virtual register " << printReg(Reg) 0
2937 << " must be live through the block.\n"; 0
2938 } ----
2939 } else { ----
2940 if (VI.AliveBlocks.test(MBB.getNumber())) { 0
2941 report("LiveVariables: Block should not be in AliveBlocks", &MBB); 0
2942 errs() << "Virtual register " << printReg(Reg) 0
2943 << " is not needed live through the block.\n"; 0
2944 } ----
2945 } ----
2946 } ----
2947 } ----
2948 } 0
2949 ----
2950 void MachineVerifier::verifyLiveIntervals() { 0
2951 assert(LiveInts && "Don't call verifyLiveIntervals without LiveInts"); 0
2952 for (unsigned I = 0, E = MRI->getNumVirtRegs(); I != E; ++I) { 0
2953 Register Reg = Register::index2VirtReg(I); 0
2954 ----
2955 // Spilling and splitting may leave unused registers around. Skip them. ----
2956 if (MRI->reg_nodbg_empty(Reg)) 0
2957 continue; 0
2958 ----
2959 if (!LiveInts->hasInterval(Reg)) { 0
2960 report("Missing live interval for virtual register", MF); 0
2961 errs() << printReg(Reg, TRI) << " still has defs or uses\n"; 0
2962 continue; 0
2963 } ----
2964 ----
2965 const LiveInterval &LI = LiveInts->getInterval(Reg); 0
2966 assert(Reg == LI.reg() && "Invalid reg to interval mapping"); 0
2967 verifyLiveInterval(LI); 0
2968 } ----
2969 ----
2970 // Verify all the cached regunit intervals. ----
2971 for (unsigned i = 0, e = TRI->getNumRegUnits(); i != e; ++i) 0
2972 if (const LiveRange *LR = LiveInts->getCachedRegUnit(i)) 0
2973 verifyLiveRange(*LR, i); 0
2974 } 0
2975 ----
2976 void MachineVerifier::verifyLiveRangeValue(const LiveRange &LR, 0
2977 const VNInfo *VNI, Register Reg, ----
2978 LaneBitmask LaneMask) { ----
2979 if (VNI->isUnused()) 0
2980 return; 0
2981 ----
2982 const VNInfo *DefVNI = LR.getVNInfoAt(VNI->def); 0
2983 ----
2984 if (!DefVNI) { 0
2985 report("Value not live at VNInfo def and not marked unused", MF); 0
2986 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
2987 report_context(*VNI); 0
2988 return; 0
2989 } ----
2990 ----
2991 if (DefVNI != VNI) { 0
2992 report("Live segment at def has different VNInfo", MF); 0
2993 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
2994 report_context(*VNI); 0
2995 return; 0
2996 } ----
2997 ----
2998 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB = LiveInts->getMBBFromIndex(VNI->def); 0
2999 if (!MBB) { 0
3000 report("Invalid VNInfo definition index", MF); 0
3001 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3002 report_context(*VNI); 0
3003 return; 0
3004 } ----
3005 ----
3006 if (VNI->isPHIDef()) { 0
3007 if (VNI->def != LiveInts->getMBBStartIdx(MBB)) { 0
3008 report("PHIDef VNInfo is not defined at MBB start", MBB); 0
3009 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3010 report_context(*VNI); 0
3011 } ----
3012 return; 0
3013 } ----
3014 ----
3015 // Non-PHI def. ----
3016 const MachineInstr *MI = LiveInts->getInstructionFromIndex(VNI->def); 0
3017 if (!MI) { 0
3018 report("No instruction at VNInfo def index", MBB); 0
3019 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3020 report_context(*VNI); 0
3021 return; 0
3022 } ----
3023 ----
3024 if (Reg != 0) { 0
3025 bool hasDef = false; 0
3026 bool isEarlyClobber = false; 0
3027 for (ConstMIBundleOperands MOI(*MI); MOI.isValid(); ++MOI) { 0
3028 if (!MOI->isReg() || !MOI->isDef()) 0
3029 continue; 0
3030 if (Reg.isVirtual()) { 0
3031 if (MOI->getReg() != Reg) 0
3032 continue; 0
3033 } else { ----
3034 if (!MOI->getReg().isPhysical() || !TRI->hasRegUnit(MOI->getReg(), Reg)) 0
3035 continue; 0
3036 } ----
3037 if (LaneMask.any() && 0
3038 (TRI->getSubRegIndexLaneMask(MOI->getSubReg()) & LaneMask).none()) 0
3039 continue; 0
3040 hasDef = true; 0
3041 if (MOI->isEarlyClobber()) 0
3042 isEarlyClobber = true; 0
3043 } ----
3044 ----
3045 if (!hasDef) { 0
3046 report("Defining instruction does not modify register", MI); 0
3047 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3048 report_context(*VNI); 0
3049 } ----
3050 ----
3051 // Early clobber defs begin at USE slots, but other defs must begin at ----
3052 // DEF slots. ----
3053 if (isEarlyClobber) { 0
3054 if (!VNI->def.isEarlyClobber()) { 0
3055 report("Early clobber def must be at an early-clobber slot", MBB); 0
3056 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3057 report_context(*VNI); 0
3058 } ----
3059 } else if (!VNI->def.isRegister()) { 0
3060 report("Non-PHI, non-early clobber def must be at a register slot", MBB); 0
3061 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3062 report_context(*VNI); 0
3063 } ----
3064 } ----
3065 } ----
3066 ----
3067 void MachineVerifier::verifyLiveRangeSegment(const LiveRange &LR, 0
3068 const LiveRange::const_iterator I, ----
3069 Register Reg, ----
3070 LaneBitmask LaneMask) { ----
3071 const LiveRange::Segment &S = *I; 0
3072 const VNInfo *VNI = S.valno; 0
3073 assert(VNI && "Live segment has no valno"); 0
3074 ----
3075 if (VNI->id >= LR.getNumValNums() || VNI != LR.getValNumInfo(VNI->id)) { 0
3076 report("Foreign valno in live segment", MF); 0
3077 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3078 report_context(S); 0
3079 report_context(*VNI); 0
3080 } ----
3081 ----
3082 if (VNI->isUnused()) { 0
3083 report("Live segment valno is marked unused", MF); 0
3084 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3085 report_context(S); 0
3086 } ----
3087 ----
3088 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB = LiveInts->getMBBFromIndex(S.start); 0
3089 if (!MBB) { 0
3090 report("Bad start of live segment, no basic block", MF); 0
3091 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3092 report_context(S); 0
3093 return; 0
3094 } ----
3095 SlotIndex MBBStartIdx = LiveInts->getMBBStartIdx(MBB); 0
3096 if (S.start != MBBStartIdx && S.start != VNI->def) { 0
3097 report("Live segment must begin at MBB entry or valno def", MBB); 0
3098 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3099 report_context(S); 0
3100 } ----
3101 ----
3102 const MachineBasicBlock *EndMBB = ----
3103 LiveInts->getMBBFromIndex(S.end.getPrevSlot()); 0
3104 if (!EndMBB) { 0
3105 report("Bad end of live segment, no basic block", MF); 0
3106 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3107 report_context(S); 0
3108 return; 0
3109 } ----
3110 ----
3111 // Checks for non-live-out segments. ----
3112 if (S.end != LiveInts->getMBBEndIdx(EndMBB)) { 0
3113 // RegUnit intervals are allowed dead phis. ----
3114 if (!Reg.isVirtual() && VNI->isPHIDef() && S.start == VNI->def && 0
3115 S.end == VNI->def.getDeadSlot()) 0
3116 return; 0
3117 ----
3118 // The live segment is ending inside EndMBB ----
3119 const MachineInstr *MI = ----
3120 LiveInts->getInstructionFromIndex(S.end.getPrevSlot()); 0
3121 if (!MI) { 0
3122 report("Live segment doesn't end at a valid instruction", EndMBB); 0
3123 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3124 report_context(S); 0
3125 return; 0
3126 } ----
3127 ----
3128 // The block slot must refer to a basic block boundary. ----
3129 if (S.end.isBlock()) { 0
3130 report("Live segment ends at B slot of an instruction", EndMBB); 0
3131 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3132 report_context(S); 0
3133 } ----
3134 ----
3135 if (S.end.isDead()) { 0
3136 // Segment ends on the dead slot. ----
3137 // That means there must be a dead def. ----
3138 if (!SlotIndex::isSameInstr(S.start, S.end)) { 0
3139 report("Live segment ending at dead slot spans instructions", EndMBB); 0
3140 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3141 report_context(S); 0
3142 } ----
3143 } ----
3144 ----
3145 // After tied operands are rewritten, a live segment can only end at an ----
3146 // early-clobber slot if it is being redefined by an early-clobber def. ----
3147 // TODO: Before tied operands are rewritten, a live segment can only end at ----
3148 // an early-clobber slot if the last use is tied to an early-clobber def. ----
3149 if (MF->getProperties().hasProperty( 0
3150 MachineFunctionProperties::Property::TiedOpsRewritten) && 0
3151 S.end.isEarlyClobber()) { 0
3152 if (I + 1 == LR.end() || (I + 1)->start != S.end) { 0
3153 report("Live segment ending at early clobber slot must be " 0
3154 "redefined by an EC def in the same instruction", ----
3155 EndMBB); ----
3156 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3157 report_context(S); 0
3158 } ----
3159 } ----
3160 ----
3161 // The following checks only apply to virtual registers. Physreg liveness ----
3162 // is too weird to check. ----
3163 if (Reg.isVirtual()) { 0
3164 // A live segment can end with either a redefinition, a kill flag on a ----
3165 // use, or a dead flag on a def. ----
3166 bool hasRead = false; 0
3167 bool hasSubRegDef = false; 0
3168 bool hasDeadDef = false; 0
3169 for (ConstMIBundleOperands MOI(*MI); MOI.isValid(); ++MOI) { 0
3170 if (!MOI->isReg() || MOI->getReg() != Reg) 0
3171 continue; 0
3172 unsigned Sub = MOI->getSubReg(); 0
3173 LaneBitmask SLM = ----
3174 Sub != 0 ? TRI->getSubRegIndexLaneMask(Sub) : LaneBitmask::getAll(); 0
3175 if (MOI->isDef()) { 0
3176 if (Sub != 0) { 0
3177 hasSubRegDef = true; 0
3178 // An operand %0:sub0 reads %0:sub1..n. Invert the lane ----
3179 // mask for subregister defs. Read-undef defs will be handled by ----
3180 // readsReg below. ----
3181 SLM = ~SLM; 0
3182 } ----
3183 if (MOI->isDead()) 0
3184 hasDeadDef = true; 0
3185 } ----
3186 if (LaneMask.any() && (LaneMask & SLM).none()) 0
3187 continue; 0
3188 if (MOI->readsReg()) 0
3189 hasRead = true; 0
3190 } ----
3191 if (S.end.isDead()) { 0
3192 // Make sure that the corresponding machine operand for a "dead" live ----
3193 // range has the dead flag. We cannot perform this check for subregister ----
3194 // liveranges as partially dead values are allowed. ----
3195 if (LaneMask.none() && !hasDeadDef) { 0
3196 report( 0
3197 "Instruction ending live segment on dead slot has no dead flag", ----
3198 MI); ----
3199 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3200 report_context(S); 0
3201 } ----
3202 } else { ----
3203 if (!hasRead) { 0
3204 // When tracking subregister liveness, the main range must start new ----
3205 // values on partial register writes, even if there is no read. ----
3206 if (!MRI->shouldTrackSubRegLiveness(Reg) || LaneMask.any() || 0
3207 !hasSubRegDef) { 0
3208 report("Instruction ending live segment doesn't read the register", 0
3209 MI); ----
3210 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3211 report_context(S); 0
3212 } ----
3213 } ----
3214 } ----
3215 } ----
3216 } ----
3217 ----
3218 // Now check all the basic blocks in this live segment. ----
3219 MachineFunction::const_iterator MFI = MBB->getIterator(); 0
3220 // Is this live segment the beginning of a non-PHIDef VN? ----
3221 if (S.start == VNI->def && !VNI->isPHIDef()) { 0
3222 // Not live-in to any blocks. ----
3223 if (MBB == EndMBB) 0
3224 return; 0
3225 // Skip this block. ----
3226 ++MFI; 0
3227 } ----
3228 ----
3229 SmallVector Undefs; 0
3230 if (LaneMask.any()) { 0
3231 LiveInterval &OwnerLI = LiveInts->getInterval(Reg); 0
3232 OwnerLI.computeSubRangeUndefs(Undefs, LaneMask, *MRI, *Indexes); 0
3233 } ----
3234 ----
3235 while (true) { ----
3236 assert(LiveInts->isLiveInToMBB(LR, &*MFI)); 0
3237 // We don't know how to track physregs into a landing pad. ----
3238 if (!Reg.isVirtual() && MFI->isEHPad()) { 0
3239 if (&*MFI == EndMBB) 0
3240 break; 0
3241 ++MFI; 0
3242 continue; 0
3243 } ----
3244 ----
3245 // Is VNI a PHI-def in the current block? ----
3246 bool IsPHI = VNI->isPHIDef() && 0
3247 VNI->def == LiveInts->getMBBStartIdx(&*MFI); 0
3248 ----
3249 // Check that VNI is live-out of all predecessors. ----
3250 for (const MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MFI->predecessors()) { 0
3251 SlotIndex PEnd = LiveInts->getMBBEndIdx(Pred); 0
3252 // Predecessor of landing pad live-out on last call. ----
3253 if (MFI->isEHPad()) { 0
3254 for (const MachineInstr &MI : llvm::reverse(*Pred)) { 0
3255 if (MI.isCall()) { 0
3256 PEnd = Indexes->getInstructionIndex(MI).getBoundaryIndex(); 0
3257 break; 0
3258 } ----
3259 } ----
3260 } ----
3261 const VNInfo *PVNI = LR.getVNInfoBefore(PEnd); 0
3262 ----
3263 // All predecessors must have a live-out value. However for a phi ----
3264 // instruction with subregister intervals ----
3265 // only one of the subregisters (not necessarily the current one) needs to ----
3266 // be defined. ----
3267 if (!PVNI && (LaneMask.none() || !IsPHI)) { 0
3268 if (LiveRangeCalc::isJointlyDominated(Pred, Undefs, *Indexes)) 0
3269 continue; 0
3270 report("Register not marked live out of predecessor", Pred); 0
3271 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3272 report_context(*VNI); 0
3273 errs() << " live into " << printMBBReference(*MFI) << '@' 0
3274 << LiveInts->getMBBStartIdx(&*MFI) << ", not live before " 0
3275 << PEnd << '\n'; 0
3276 continue; 0
3277 } ----
3278 ----
3279 // Only PHI-defs can take different predecessor values. ----
3280 if (!IsPHI && PVNI != VNI) { 0
3281 report("Different value live out of predecessor", Pred); 0
3282 report_context(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3283 errs() << "Valno #" << PVNI->id << " live out of " 0
3284 << printMBBReference(*Pred) << '@' << PEnd << "\nValno #" 0
3285 << VNI->id << " live into " << printMBBReference(*MFI) << '@' 0
3286 << LiveInts->getMBBStartIdx(&*MFI) << '\n'; 0
3287 } ----
3288 } ----
3289 if (&*MFI == EndMBB) 0
3290 break; 0
3291 ++MFI; 0
3292 } 0
3293 } 0
3294 ----
3295 void MachineVerifier::verifyLiveRange(const LiveRange &LR, Register Reg, 0
3296 LaneBitmask LaneMask) { ----
3297 for (const VNInfo *VNI : LR.valnos) 0
3298 verifyLiveRangeValue(LR, VNI, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3299 ----
3300 for (LiveRange::const_iterator I = LR.begin(), E = LR.end(); I != E; ++I) 0
3301 verifyLiveRangeSegment(LR, I, Reg, LaneMask); 0
3302 } 0
3303 ----
3304 void MachineVerifier::verifyLiveInterval(const LiveInterval &LI) { 0
3305 Register Reg = LI.reg(); 0
3306 assert(Reg.isVirtual()); 0
3307 verifyLiveRange(LI, Reg); 0
3308 ----
3309 LaneBitmask Mask; 0
3310 LaneBitmask MaxMask = MRI->getMaxLaneMaskForVReg(Reg); 0
3311 for (const LiveInterval::SubRange &SR : LI.subranges()) { 0
3312 if ((Mask & SR.LaneMask).any()) { 0
3313 report("Lane masks of sub ranges overlap in live interval", MF); 0
3314 report_context(LI); 0
3315 } ----
3316 if ((SR.LaneMask & ~MaxMask).any()) { 0
3317 report("Subrange lanemask is invalid", MF); 0
3318 report_context(LI); 0
3319 } ----
3320 if (SR.empty()) { 0
3321 report("Subrange must not be empty", MF); 0
3322 report_context(SR, LI.reg(), SR.LaneMask); 0
3323 } ----
3324 Mask |= SR.LaneMask; 0
3325 verifyLiveRange(SR, LI.reg(), SR.LaneMask); 0
3326 if (!LI.covers(SR)) { 0
3327 report("A Subrange is not covered by the main range", MF); 0
3328 report_context(LI); 0
3329 } ----
3330 } ----
3331 ----
3332 // Check the LI only has one connected component. ----
3333 ConnectedVNInfoEqClasses ConEQ(*LiveInts); 0
3334 unsigned NumComp = ConEQ.Classify(LI); 0
3335 if (NumComp > 1) { 0
3336 report("Multiple connected components in live interval", MF); 0
3337 report_context(LI); 0
3338 for (unsigned comp = 0; comp != NumComp; ++comp) { 0
3339 errs() << comp << ": valnos"; 0
3340 for (const VNInfo *I : LI.valnos) 0
3341 if (comp == ConEQ.getEqClass(I)) 0
3342 errs() << ' ' << I->id; 0
3343 errs() << '\n'; 0
3344 } ----
3345 } ----
3346 } 0
3347 ----
3348 namespace { ----
3349 ----
3350 // FrameSetup and FrameDestroy can have zero adjustment, so using a single ----
3351 // integer, we can't tell whether it is a FrameSetup or FrameDestroy if the ----
3352 // value is zero. ----
3353 // We use a bool plus an integer to capture the stack state. ----
3354 struct StackStateOfBB { ----
3355 StackStateOfBB() = default; 0
3356 StackStateOfBB(int EntryVal, int ExitVal, bool EntrySetup, bool ExitSetup) : ----
3357 EntryValue(EntryVal), ExitValue(ExitVal), EntryIsSetup(EntrySetup), ----
3358 ExitIsSetup(ExitSetup) {} ----
3359 ----
3360 // Can be negative, which means we are setting up a frame. ----
3361 int EntryValue = 0; ----
3362 int ExitValue = 0; ----
3363 bool EntryIsSetup = false; ----
3364 bool ExitIsSetup = false; ----
3365 }; ----
3366 ----
3367 } // end anonymous namespace ----
3368 ----
3369 /// Make sure on every path through the CFG, a FrameSetup is always followed ----
3370 /// by a FrameDestroy , stack adjustments are identical on all ----
3371 /// CFG edges to a merge point, and frame is destroyed at end of a return block. ----
3372 void MachineVerifier::verifyStackFrame() { 0
3373 unsigned FrameSetupOpcode = TII->getCallFrameSetupOpcode(); 0
3374 unsigned FrameDestroyOpcode = TII->getCallFrameDestroyOpcode(); 0
3375 if (FrameSetupOpcode == ~0u && FrameDestroyOpcode == ~0u) 0
3376 return; 0
3377 ----
3378 SmallVector SPState; 0
3379 SPState.resize(MF->getNumBlockIDs()); 0
3380 df_iterator_default_set Reachable; 0
3381 ----
3382 // Visit the MBBs in DFS order. ----
3383 for (df_ext_iterator 0
3384 df_iterator_default_set> ----
3385 DFI = df_ext_begin(MF, Reachable), DFE = df_ext_end(MF, Reachable); 0
3386 DFI != DFE; ++DFI) { 0
3387 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB = *DFI; 0
3388 ----
3389 StackStateOfBB BBState; 0
3390 // Check the exit state of the DFS stack predecessor. ----
3391 if (DFI.getPathLength() >= 2) { 0
3392 const MachineBasicBlock *StackPred = DFI.getPath(DFI.getPathLength() - 2); 0
3393 assert(Reachable.count(StackPred) && 0
3394 "DFS stack predecessor is already visited.\n"); ----
3395 BBState.EntryValue = SPState[StackPred->getNumber()].ExitValue; 0
3396 BBState.EntryIsSetup = SPState[StackPred->getNumber()].ExitIsSetup; 0
3397 BBState.ExitValue = BBState.EntryValue; 0
3398 BBState.ExitIsSetup = BBState.EntryIsSetup; 0
3399 } ----
3400 ----
3401 if ((int)MBB->getCallFrameSize() != -BBState.EntryValue) { 0
3402 report("Call frame size on entry does not match value computed from " 0
3403 "predecessor", ----
3404 MBB); ----
3405 errs() << "Call frame size on entry " << MBB->getCallFrameSize() 0
3406 << " does not match value computed from predecessor " 0
3407 << -BBState.EntryValue << '\n'; 0
3408 } ----
